e de la Francophonie]]\n[[Category:Member states of the United Nations]]\n[[Category:Small Island Developing States]]\n[[Category:Former colonies in North America]]\n[[Category:British Windward Islands]]\n[[Category:French Caribbean]]\n[[Category:1800s establishments in the Caribbean]]\n[[Category:1803 establishments in North America]]\n[[Category:1803 establishments in the British Empire]]\n[[Category:States and territories established in 1979]]\n[[Category:1970s establishments in the Caribbean]]\n[[Category:1979 establishments in North America]]\n[[Category:Countries in North America]]\n", "name_user": "87.5.60.246", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eSport)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saint_Lucia"}
{"title_page": "Piaggio", "text_new": "{{coord|43.6609332|10.6304703|display=title}}\n{{for|the aircraft manufacturer|Piaggio Aerospace}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2017}}\n\n{{Infobox company\n| name                = Piaggio & C. SpA\n| logo                = [[File:Piaggiogrouplogo.png|frameless|upright=0.9]]\n| type                = Public company\n| traded_as           = {{BIT|isin=IT0003073266|PIA}}\n| predecessor         = \n| successor           = \n| founder             = Rinaldo Piaggio\n| defunct             = <!-- {{End date|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| fate                = \n| area_served         = Worldwide\n| key_people          = {{unbulleted list| Roberto Colaninno, Chairman and CEO }}\n| industry            = {{unbulleted list| Motor vehicle manufacturing | Motor vehicle distribution | Engine manufacturing }}\n| products            = \n| production          = \n| services            = \n| revenue             = {{increase}} \u20ac1,512 million (2019)<ref name=\"Annual Results 2019\">{{cite web |title=Piaggio Group: 2018 Draft Financial Statements |url=https://www.piaggiogroup.com/en/archive/press/piaggio-group-2018-draft-financial-statements1-0|website=Piaggio Group |accessdate=06 April 2018 |language=en |date=26 Feb 2020}}</ref>\n| net_income          = {{increase}} \u20ac46.7&nbsp;million (2019)<ref name=\"Annual Results 2019\"/>\n| assets              = \n| equity              = \n| owner               = \n| num_employees       = 7,510 <ref>{{cite web |title=Piaggio Group: 2014 draft financial statements |url=http://www.piaggiogroup.com/en/archive/press/piaggio-group-2014-draft-financial-statements |website=Piaggio Group |accessdate= 22 September 2018 |language=en |date=27 February 2015}}</ref>\n| parent              = \n| divisions           = \n| subsid              = {{unbulleted list | [[Aprilia]] | [[Derbi]] | [[Gilera]] | [[Moto Guzzi]] | Piaggio | [[Vespa]]| Piaggio - commercial vehicles}}\n| homepage            = {{URL|piaggiogroup.com/en}}\n| footnotes           = \n| caption             = \n| former type         = \n| foundation          = {{start date and age|1884|01|24|df=yes}}\n| location_city       = [[Pontedera]]\n| location_country    = Italy\n| locations           = <!-- Number of retail dealers -->\n| operating_income    = {{increase}} \u20ac124.8nbsp;million (2019)<ref name=\"Annual Results 2019\" />\n}}\n\n'''Piaggio & C. SpA''' (Piaggio {{IPA-it|\u02c8pjadd\u0292o|}}) is an [[Italy|Italian]] motor vehicle manufacturer, which produces a range of two-wheeled [[motor vehicle]]s and compact commercial vehicles under seven brands: Piaggio, [[Vespa]], [[Gilera]], [[Aprilia]], [[Moto Guzzi]], [[Derbi]], and Scarabeo. Its corporate headquarters are located in [[Pontedera]], Italy. The company was founded by [[Rinaldo Piaggio]] in 1884, initially producing locomotives and railway carriages.\n\nPiaggio's subsidiaries employ a total of 7,053 employees and produced a total of 519,700 vehicles in 2014.<ref name=\"Annual Results 2015\" /> The manufacturer has six research-and-development centers and operates in over 50 countries.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://piaggio2012.message-asp.com/en/piaggio-and-research-and-development |title=Annual Report 2012 \u2013 Piaggio Group |access-date=3 October 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004221733/http://piaggio2012.message-asp.com/en/piaggio-and-research-and-development |archive-date=4 October 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==History==\nIn 1882, Enrico Piaggio purchased land in [[Sestri Ponente]] ([[Genoa]]) to set up a timber yard. Two years later, in 1884, his 20-year-old son, [[:it:Rinaldo Piaggio|Rinaldo Piaggio]], founded Piaggio & C. The company initially built locomotives and railway carriages but in 1917, towards the end of [[World War I|World War]], Rinaldo Piaggio turned to the military sector. To begin with, the company produced MAS anti-[[submarine]] motorboats, [[aeroplanes]] and [[seaplane]]s under [[Ansaldo STS|Ansaldo]], [[Macchi]], [[Caproni]], and [[Dornier Flugzeugwerke|Dornier]] [[license]]s but later progressed to vehicles constructed according Piaggio's own drawings.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GZleYU_uSeAC&pg=PA15&lpg=PA15&dq=rinaldo+piaggio+submarine+motorboats,+and+aeroplanes+and+seaplanes&source=bl&ots=Hf6rYhK9I3&sig=Ncl-FMw1S8gIo-MwKlRb1VjqgsE&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjrh4_N79rcAhXGsY8KHTCaBuwQ6AEwDXoECAYQAQ#v=onepage&q=rinaldo%20piaggio%20submarine%20motorboats,%20and%20aeroplanes%20and%20seaplanes&f=false|title=Vespa|last=Sarti|first=Giorgio|date=2006|publisher=Motorbooks|isbn=9780760325773|language=en}}</ref>\n\nBetween 1937 and 1939 Piaggio achieved 21 world records with its aircraft and engines built at the company's new factory in [[Pontedera]], culminating in the four-engine [[Piaggio P.108]] bomber.\n\nRinaldo died in 1938, by which time Piaggio was owned by multiple shareholders within the family, along with the entrepreneur [[:it:Attilio Odero|Attilio Odero]]. Management of the company passed to his sons [[Enrico Piaggio|Enrico]] and Armando.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.referenceforbusiness.com/history2/83/Piaggio-C-S-p-A.html |title = History of Piaggio & C. S.p.A.}}</ref>\n\nBy 1940 Piaggio was manufacturing trains, [[nautical]] fittings, [[aircraft engine]]s, aeroplanes, trucks, trams, buses, [[funicular]]s and aluminium windows and doors. The [[Pontedera]] plant was destroyed by Allied bombing and production activities were relocated to the [[Biella]] area. After the war, Enrico Piaggio decided to diversify the company's activities outside the aeronautical industry to address a perceived need for a modern, affordable mode of transport for the Italian mass market. The first attempt, based on a small [[motorcycle]] made for [[Parachuting|parachutists]], was known as the MP5 and nicknamed the \"[[Paperino]]\" (the Italian name for [[Donald Duck]]) because of its strange shape. Ultimately Enrico Piaggio did not like it and asked [[Corradino D'Ascanio]] to redesign it.\n\nD'Ascanio, an aeronautical engineer responsible for the design and construction of the first modern helicopter by [[Agusta]], was not naturally enthusiastic about [[motorcycle]]s, judging them to be uncomfortable and bulky, with wheels that were difficult to change after a puncture. When asked to design a motorcycle for [[Ferdinando Innocenti]], D'Ascanio had come up with a step through scooter design but D'Ascanio and Innocenti disagreed over use of pressings rather than tubing so D'Ascanio brought his design to Piaggio. Innocenti would ultimately use D'Ascanio's original design for their [[Lambretta]] scooter.\n\nPiaggio asked D'Ascanio to create a simple, robust and affordable vehicle. The [[motorcycle]] had to be easy to drive for both men and women, be able to carry a passenger, and not get its driver's clothes dirty. The engineer's drawings proved a significant departure from the Paperino. With the help of [[Mario D'Este]] he prepared the first Vespa project, manufactured at Piaggio newly-rebuilt Pontedera headquarters in April 1946. Piaggio launched the [[Vespa]] (Italian for \"wasp\") and within ten years more than a million units had been produced. The Italian language gained a new word, \"vespare\", meaning to go somewhere on a Vespa.<ref>{{cite web |url = https://ultimatemotorcycling.com/2010/08/29/piaggio-origins-and-vespa-history/ |title = Piaggio Origins & Vespa History}}</ref>\n\n===Ownership===\n[[File:Vespa a Todi.JPG|thumbnail|[[Vespa]] in a Todi street]]\nVespa thrived until 1992 when [[Gianni Agnelli]] became CEO. Agnelli was already suffering from cancer and died in 2003. In 1999 [[Morgan Grenfell Private Equity]] acquired Piaggio, but hopes for a quick sale were dashed by a failed joint venture in China.{{Clarify|date=February 2013}} In Italy, Piaggio invested 15 million euros ($19.4&nbsp;million) in a new motorcycle but dropped it after building a prototype. By the end of 2002, the company had run up 577&nbsp;million Euros in debt on revenues of 945&nbsp;million Euros, and booked a loss of 129&nbsp;million Euros.\n\nIn 2003 Piaggio's debt was reduced a 100 million Euro investment made by [[:it:IMMSI|IMMSI]], a holding company of the Colaninno family. 150&nbsp;million shares were also converted by creditor banks. Reflecting on his investment, [[:it:Roberto Colaninno|Roberto Colaninno]] said,\n\n\"A lot of people told me I was crazy. Piaggio wasn't dying. It just needed to be treated better.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB114947493428871213|title=Vespa's Builder Scoots Back To Profitability}}</ref>\"\n\n[[Roberto Colaninno|Colannino]] became the new chairman of Piaggio, while Dr. Rocco Sabelli becoming the managing director. Sabelli redesigned the production line according to Japanese principles so that every Piaggio scooter could be made on any assembly line. Contrary to expectations, Mr. Colaninno did not fire a single worker \u2013 a move which helped seduce the company's skeptical unions. \"Everyone in a company is part of the value chain,\" said Colaninno. All bonuses for blue-collar workers and management were based on the same criteria: profit margins and customer satisfaction. Air conditioning was installed in the factory for the first time, increasing productivity. He also gave the company's engineers, who had been idled by the company's financial crisis, deadlines for projects. They rolled out two world firsts in 2004: a gas-electric hybrid scooter and a sophisticated tilting scooter with two wheels in front and one in back to grip the road better.\n\nOne of Piaggio's problems Mr. Colaninno couldn't fix from the inside was its scale. Even though Piaggio was the European market leader, it was dwarfed by rivals [[Honda]] and [[Yamaha Motor Company|Yamaha]]. A year after restoring Piaggio's health, Colaninno directed Piaggio's takeover of the Italian scooter and motorcycle manufacturer [[Aprilia]], and with it the Aprilia-owned [[Moto Guzzi]], a storied Italian manufacturer of motorcycles.\n\nIn 2006, Piaggio floated on the [[Milan Stock Exchange]], becoming a public company.\n\n===Production Development===\nIn 1956, with production of the millionth [[Vespa]] scooter, Italy had its first mass-produced motorised vehicle. Taking advantage of increased cash flow thanks to the success of the Vespa, Piaggio developed other products, including the 1957 [[Vespa 400]], a compact passenger car.\n\nIn 1959 Piaggio came under the control of the [[Agnelli family]], the owners of car maker [[Fiat|Fiat SpA]].\n\nBy 1960 Vespa had produced and sold 4 million units worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|language = en|url = http://www.museopiaggio.it/en/history/|title = Piaggio History}}</ref>\n\nIn 1964 the aeronautical and motorcycle divisions of Piaggio split to become two independent companies as a result of the wide ownership by Fiat in Italian industry.{{Clarify|date=February 2013}} The aeronautical division was named IAM Rinaldo Piaggio. The aircraft company [[Piaggio Aero]] was controlled by the family of Piero Ferrari, who still hold 10% of [[Ferrari]].\n\nIn 1969 Piaggio purchased the motorcycle company [[Gilera]], one of the oldest European motorcycle manufacturers (founded in 1909), famous for its sporting achievements and world titles in the [[Motocycle World Championship|Motorcycle World Championship]].<ref>{{cite web|language = en|url = https://www.autoevolution.com/moto/gilera/|title = Gilera \u2013 Models and History}}</ref>\n\nIn 1971 a steering wheel was added to the [[Piaggio Ape]], a model first produced in 1948, culminating in the Ape Car. Four years later, in 1975, the company made the first prototype of an electric Ape.<ref>{{cite web|language = en|url = http://www.tukxi.com/history.html|title = History of Piaggio Ape}}</ref>\n\nIn 1988 the Vespa reached the milestone of 10 million units produced.<ref>{{cite web|language = en|url = https://www.mirror.co.uk/lifestyle/motoring/happy-days-vespa-celebrates-70th-7850941|title = Happy Days! Vespa celebrates its 70th birthday}}</ref>\n\nIn 1996, on the fiftieth anniversary of the first model, [[Vespa]] passed 15 million units produced and the new 4-stroke Vespa ET, the first completely new Vespa for 18 years, was launched.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vespa.com/en_EN/Heritage.html|title=Vespa History}}</ref> Piaggio was still in poor financial health but its brand recognition remained strong, boosted by the appearance of the ET4 in several Hollywood films.\n\nIn 1999, in [[Baramati]], production began on a three-wheeler Ape for the [[India]]n domestic market.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.motoroids.com/news/piaggio-inaugurates-vespa-manufacturing-plant-in-baramati/|title=Piaggio inaugurates Vespa manufacturing plant in Baramati}}</ref>\n\nIn 2000 Piaggio and Vespa returned to the United States with the opening of the first Vespa Boutique in Los Angeles. In that same year the Piaggio Historical Museum was inaugurated in [[Pontedera]]. The museum showcases the Piaggio Historical Archive, one of the most comprehensive company archives on the industrial history of Italy.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.museopiaggio.it/en/|title=Piaggio Museum}}</ref>\n\nIn 2001 the Piaggio Group acquired Derbi-Nacional Motor SA,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.piaggiogroup.com/en/group/brands/derbi|title=Derbi}}</ref> an historical Spanish brand founded in 1922 that had won 18 world titles and was a continental leader in the small displacement motorbike segment. In the same year [[Gilera]] returned to the [[Motorcycle World Championship]] and immediately won the world title in the 125 category with Manuel Poggiali.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.motogp.com/en/news/2001/05/21/poggiali-brings-gilera-first-125-win-for-45-years/130710|title=Poggiali brings Gilera first 125 win for 45 years}}</ref>\n\nIn 2004, at the end of December, the final contract for the acquisition of the [[Aprilia]]-[[Moto Guzzi Group]] was signed. The most important European two-wheeler group is born.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.webbikeworld.com/motorcycle-news/piaggio-aprilia.htm|title=Piaggio Buys Aprilia & Moto Guzzi}}</ref>\n\nIn 2007 Piaggio Group officially arrives in [[Vietnam]]. The Vinh Puch plant includes R&D, welding and painting activities, as well as final assembly of the scooters, with warehouse, testing, quality control and office areas.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.piaggiogroup.com/en/archive/press/piaggio-group-official-opening-new-vietnam-factory|title=Piaggio Group: official opening of new Vietnam factory}}</ref>\n\nIn 2009 the Piaggio Mp3 Hybrid makes its debut on the market which was first hybrid scooter in the world, integrating the conventional low-environmental-impact internal combustion engine with a zero-emission electric motor and combining the advantages of the two power trains.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.autoblog.com/2010/07/07/piaggio-launches-mp3-hybrid-300ie-scooter/|title=Piaggio launches MP3 Hybrid 300ie scooter}}</ref>\n\nIn [[Baramati]] (State of [[Maharashtra]]), in 2012, the Piaggio Group's new plant for the production of Vespa's for the local market was opened.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.piaggiogroup.com/en/archive/press/piaggio-group-vespa-makes-its-official-debut-indian-market|title=Piaggio Group: Vespa makes its official debut on the Indian market}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013 the PADC \u2013 Piaggio Advanced Design Center opened in [[Pasadena]] (California, United States).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cycleworld.com/2012/04/17/will-the-motorcycle-of-the-future-come-from-pasadena|title=Will The Motorcycle of the Future Come From Pasadena?}}</ref> The Vespa 946 was also launched this year, along with the new Vespa Primavera, the latest evolution of the \"small body\" family.\n\nIn 2013 Vespa's worldwide sales numbered almost 190,000 units; in 2004 the figure stood at 58,000. In ten years of continuous progression over 1.3&nbsp;million new Vespas have reached the streets of the world. Since 1946 over 18 million Vespas have been produced and sold.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.news18.com/news/auto/70-years-of-vespa-all-the-vespas-produced-ever-1233703.html|title=70 Years of Vespa: All the Vespas Produced, Ever}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2017 Foton and Piaggio agreed to form a joint venture to develop and produce light commercial vehicle.<ref>[http://www.piaggiocommercialvehicles.com/it_IT/news-list/partnership-piaggio-foton/ Piaggio and Foton joint venture]</ref> Based on Foton chassis the new vehicle was sold by [[Piaggio Commercial Vehicle]] division in Europe and in all markets around the world but not in China. The vehicle is intended to be a successor of the [[Piaggio Porter]] and production is planned to start in mid-2019 in [[Pontedera]] ([[Italy]]) with all components produced by Foton in China.<ref>[http://www.repubblica.it/economia/finanza/2018/04/16/news/piaggio_all_accordo_con_i_cinesi_di_foton-194028229/ Piaggio Accordo con Foton per il nuovo Porter]</ref>\n\n== \"Cultural Project\" Piaggio ==\nPiaggio's \"cultural project\" promotes the reconstruction and enhancement of the company's heritage and is composed by three initiatives:  the Piaggio Foundation, the Historical Archives and the Piaggio Museum. In 2003 the Museum and Archives were recognised as the Best Corporate Museum and Archive by winning the Italian prize \"Premio Impresa e Cultura\".<ref>[http://www.piaggiogroup.com/en/node/4531]{{dead link|date=February 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\nIn 2016, under the patronage of the [[Ministry of Cultural Heritage and Activities and Tourism (Italy)|Italian Ministry of Culture]], Piaggio received the [[Corporate Art Awards|Corporate Art Award]] from [[pptArt]] for its Corporate Museum.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pptart.net/winners|title=2016 Corporate Art Awards - Corporate winners}}</ref>\n\n==Brands and models==\n[[File:Light blue Vespa GL, front.jpg|thumb|upright|1962 Vespa 150 GL]]\n[[File:Piaggio mp3.jpg|thumb|Piaggio MP3 three-wheel scooter]]\n\n===Group brands===\n* [[Aprilia]] \u2013 motorcycles, [[scooter (motorcycle)|scooter]] and [[moped]]s\n* Piaggio \u2013 scooters, mopeds.\n* [[Vespa]] \u2013 scooters and mopeds\n* [[Scarabeo]] \u2013 scooters and mopeds\n* [[Derbi]] \u2013 motorcycles, scooters, mopeds and recreational [[All-terrain vehicle|ATV]]s (''quads'')\n* [[Gilera]] \u2013 motorcycles, scooters, mopeds and recreational [[All-terrain vehicle|ATV]]s (''quads'')\n* [[Moto Guzzi]] \u2013 motorcycles\n* [[Piaggio Commercial Vehicles]] \u2013  [[light commercial vehicle]]s\n\n===Models===\n[[File:Piaggio Grillo a Rovigo.jpg|thumb|[[Piaggio Grillo]].]]\n* Piaggio 110 Bicycle bodywork(110 anniversaries)\n* [[Piaggio Ape|Ape]] \u2013 3-wheel micro [[light commercial vehicle]]s\n* [[Piaggio Porter]] 4-wheel [[microvan]]s and micro-[[pickup truck|pickup]]s, same as a [[Daihatsu Hijet]].\n* [[Piaggio Quargo]] 4-wheel [[microvan]]s and micro-[[pickup truck|pickup]]s,\n* [[Piaggio MP3]] tilting 3-wheel scooter\n* Diesis 50/100 (50cc air-cooled [[2-stroke]] and 100&nbsp;cc water-cooled 2-stroke) made between 2001 and 2005\n* FLY50/100/125/150\n* Free50\n* Typhoon 50&nbsp;cc, 80&nbsp;cc, 125&nbsp;cc (1995\u20132000;2012)\n* Sfera NSL (50&nbsp;cc & 80&nbsp;cc) 1991\u20131995\n* Sfera RST (RST standing for Restyle) (50&nbsp;cc 2-stroke & 125&nbsp;cc 4-stroke) 1995 \u2013 ??\n* [[Piaggio NRG|NRG mc1-3]] (50&nbsp;cc) (mc standing for mark.)\n* NRG Power PureJet (50&nbsp;cc fuel injection, water cooling)\n* NRG Power DT (air-cooled) and DD (liquid-cooled), both introduced in 2005\n* NTT (water-cooled 2-stroke) made between 1995 and 1998\n* Liberty (50&nbsp;cc 2-stroke, 125&nbsp; cc & 150&nbsp;cc Quattrotempi)\n* Liberty S (50&nbsp;cc 125&nbsp;cc 200&nbsp;cc)\n* LT ( US models of the Liberty. 50&nbsp;cc and 125&nbsp;cc 2-stroke)\n* Skipper ST (125&nbsp;cc)\n* [[Piaggio Ciao]] (50&nbsp;cc)\n* Si (50&nbsp;cc)\n* Superbravo (50&nbsp;cc)\n* Avanti (50&nbsp;cc)\n* Grillo (50&nbsp;cc)\n* Bravo (50&nbsp;cc)\n* Grande (50&nbsp;cc)\n* Boxer (50&nbsp;cc)\n* Boxer 2 (50&nbsp;cc)\n* [[Piaggio X7|X7]] 125 (European market), 250\n* [[Piaggio X7 Evo|X7 Evo]] (125, 300&nbsp;cc) \u2013 announced 2009\n* [[Piaggio X8|X8]] 125 (European market), 250, 400\n* [[Piaggio Xevo|XEvo]] 125, 250, 400\n* X9 125/250 cc Evolution \u2013 the Evolution models superseded the previous X9 models in 2004, which were fitted with Honda engines\n* X9 500 cc Evolution with features not fitted on 125/250 cc models: hydraulic centre stand, integrated rider-to-pillion communication system, mobile-phone charger in front dash cubbyhole\n* BV200/250\n* BV350\n* BV500 \u2013 neo-classic style, automatic transmission, top-speed 100&nbsp;mph\n* [[Piaggio Beverly|Beverly]] (125&nbsp;cc; 250&nbsp;cc; 400&nbsp;cc; 500&nbsp;cc: Beverly is the Italian name for the BV models)\n* Medley 125&nbsp;cc, Medley S 125cc\n* Carnaby (125&nbsp;cc & 200&nbsp;cc)\n* Free 50 (50&nbsp;cc)\n* Hexagon (125&nbsp;cc; 150&nbsp;cc; 180&nbsp;cc; 250&nbsp;cc)\n* T (125&nbsp;cc; 150&nbsp;cc)\n* Piaggio Velofax or Vespino 1995 to 1999.\n* Quartz (50&nbsp;cc 2-stroke, liquid-cooled)\n* Quartz (125 cc, 2-stroke, air-cooled)\n* Storm (125 cc, 4-stroke, air-cooled)\n* M500 (505 cc, 2-stroke, microcar)\n* Ravi Piaggio Strom (125&nbsp;cc, 4-stroke) Joint venture of Piaggio with Ravi and available in Pakistani market\n* [[Piaggio Ape|Piaggio Ape RR]]\n* [[Piaggio Zip|Zip]] 50&nbsp;cc 2-stroke, air-cooled (pre 2000)\n* [[Piaggio Zip|Zip SP]] 50&nbsp;cc 2-stroke, water-cooled (pre 2000)\n* [[Piaggio Zip|Zip (Cat)]] 50&nbsp;cc 2-stroke, air-cooled (2000 onwards)\n* [[Piaggio Zip|Zip SP]] 50&nbsp;cc two-stroke, water-cooled (2000 onwards)\n* [[Piaggio Zip|Zip 4t]] 50&nbsp;cc 4-stroke, air-cooled\n* [[Piaggio Zip|Zip 4t 100]] 96.2&nbsp;cc 4-stroke, air-cooled\n* [[Piaggio Zip|Zip 125]] 125&nbsp;cc 4-stroke, air-cooled\n{{Expand list|date=August 2008}}\n\n===Electric scooters===\nThe new [[plug-in hybrid]] version of the [[Piaggio MP3]] will be equipped with a 125&nbsp;cc petrol engine and electric motor, which offers about {{convert|141|mpgus|abbr=on}} and travels {{convert|13|mi}} using battery power alone. This machine could be out in 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.treehugger.com/files/2008/11/piaggio-scooter.php |title=Piaggio Scooters Gone Green: 141 MPG Hybrid |publisher=TreeHugger |date= |accessdate=2009-08-10}}</ref>\n\nPiaggio/Vespa are also developing hybrid electric scooters. There are two models in the works, based on the popular [[Vespa LX 50]] and the beefier [[Piaggio X8]] 125.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.treehugger.com/files/2006/04/vespa_unveils_h.php#ch01 |title=Vespa Unveils Hybrid Scooters |publisher=TreeHugger |date= |accessdate=2009-08-10}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}<!--added above External links/Sources by script-assisted edit-->\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|Italy|Companies}}\n{{stack begin}}{{Commons category|Piaggio}}{{stack end}}\n* [http://www.piaggiogroup.com Piaggio official website]\n* [http://www.piaggiocommercialvehicles.com/ Piaggio Commercial Vehicles]\n* [https://www.museopiaggio.it/en/ Piaggio Museum - Museo Piaggio]\n{{Gilera}}\n{{Moto Guzzi}}\n{{Aprilia motorcycles}}\n{{Automotive industry in Italy}}\n{{Major Italian motorcycle manufacturers}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Italian brands]]\n[[Category:Vehicle manufacturing companies established in 1884]]\n[[Category:1884 establishments in Italy]]\n[[Category:Piaggio Group| ]]\n[[Category:Companies listed on the Borsa Italiana]]\n[[Category:Motorcycle manufacturers of Italy]]\n[[Category:Aircraft manufacturers of Italy]]\n[[Category:Aircraft engine manufacturers of Italy]]\n[[Category:Scooter manufacturers]]\n[[Category:Moped manufacturers]]\n[[Category:Plug-in hybrid vehicles]]\n[[Category:Private equity portfolio companies]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Tuscany]]\n", "text_old": "{{coord|43.6609332|10.6304703|display=title}}\n{{for|the aircraft manufacturer|Piaggio Aerospace}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2017}}\n\n{{Infobox company\n| name             = Piaggio & C. SpA\n| logo             = [[File:Piaggiogrouplogo.png|frameless|upright=0.9]]\n| type             = Public company\n| traded_as        = {{BIT|isin=IT0003073266|PIA}}\n| predecessor      = \n| successor        = \n| founder          = Rinaldo Piaggio\n| defunct          = <!-- {{End date|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| fate             = \n| area_served      = Worldwide\n| key_people       = {{unbulleted list| Roberto Colaninno, Chairman and CEO }}\n| industry         = {{unbulleted list| Motor vehicle manufacturing | Motor vehicle distribution | Engine manufacturing }}\n| products         = \n| production       = \n| services         = \n| revenue          = {{increase}} \u20ac1,295&nbsp;million (2015)<ref name=\"Annual Results 2015\">{{cite web |title=Piaggio Group: 2015 Draft Financial Statements |url=http://www.piaggiogroup.com/en/archive/press/piaggio-group-2015-draft-financial-statements |website=Piaggio Group |accessdate=22 September 2018 |language=en |date=26 May 2015}}</ref>\n| net_income       = {{increase}} \u20ac11.9&nbsp;million (2015)<ref name=\"Annual Results 2015\"/>\n| assets           = \n| equity           = \n| owner            = \n| num_employees    = 7,510 <ref>{{cite web |title=Piaggio Group: 2014 draft financial statements |url=http://www.piaggiogroup.com/en/archive/press/piaggio-group-2014-draft-financial-statements |website=Piaggio Group |accessdate= 22 September 2018 |language=en |date=27 February 2015}}</ref>\n| parent           = \n| divisions        = \n| subsid           = {{unbulleted list | [[Aprilia]] | [[Derbi]] | [[Gilera]] | [[Moto Guzzi]] | Piaggio | [[Vespa]]| Piaggio - commercial vehicles}}\n| homepage         = {{URL|piaggiogroup.com/en}}\n| footnotes        = \n| caption          =\n| former type      = \n| foundation       = {{start date and age|1884|01|24|df=yes}}\n| location_city    = [[Pontedera]]\n| location_country = Italy\n| locations        = <!-- Number of retail dealers -->\n| operating_income  = {{increase}} \u20ac161.8&nbsp;million (2015)<ref name=\"Annual Results 2015\" />\n}}\n\n'''Piaggio & C. SpA''' (Piaggio {{IPA-it|\u02c8pjadd\u0292o|}}) is an [[Italy|Italian]] motor vehicle manufacturer, which produces a range of two-wheeled [[motor vehicle]]s and compact commercial vehicles under seven brands: Piaggio, [[Vespa]], [[Gilera]], [[Aprilia]], [[Moto Guzzi]], [[Derbi]], and Scarabeo. Its corporate headquarters are located in [[Pontedera]], Italy. The company was founded by [[Rinaldo Piaggio]] in 1884, initially producing locomotives and railway carriages.\n\nPiaggio's subsidiaries employ a total of 7,053 employees and produced a total of 519,700 vehicles in 2014.<ref name=\"Annual Results 2015\" /> The manufacturer has six research-and-development centers and operates in over 50 countries.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://piaggio2012.message-asp.com/en/piaggio-and-research-and-development |title=Annual Report 2012 \u2013 Piaggio Group |access-date=3 October 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004221733/http://piaggio2012.message-asp.com/en/piaggio-and-research-and-development |archive-date=4 October 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==History==\nIn 1882, Enrico Piaggio purchased land in [[Sestri Ponente]] ([[Genoa]]) to set up a timber yard. Two years later, in 1884, his 20-year-old son, [[:it:Rinaldo Piaggio|Rinaldo Piaggio]], founded Piaggio & C. The company initially built locomotives and railway carriages but in 1917, towards the end of [[World War I|World War]], Rinaldo Piaggio turned to the military sector. To begin with, the company produced MAS anti-[[submarine]] motorboats, [[aeroplanes]] and [[seaplane]]s under [[Ansaldo STS|Ansaldo]], [[Macchi]], [[Caproni]], and [[Dornier Flugzeugwerke|Dornier]] [[license]]s but later progressed to vehicles constructed according Piaggio's own drawings.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GZleYU_uSeAC&pg=PA15&lpg=PA15&dq=rinaldo+piaggio+submarine+motorboats,+and+aeroplanes+and+seaplanes&source=bl&ots=Hf6rYhK9I3&sig=Ncl-FMw1S8gIo-MwKlRb1VjqgsE&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjrh4_N79rcAhXGsY8KHTCaBuwQ6AEwDXoECAYQAQ#v=onepage&q=rinaldo%20piaggio%20submarine%20motorboats,%20and%20aeroplanes%20and%20seaplanes&f=false|title=Vespa|last=Sarti|first=Giorgio|date=2006|publisher=Motorbooks|isbn=9780760325773|language=en}}</ref>\n\nBetween 1937 and 1939 Piaggio achieved 21 world records with its aircraft and engines built at the company's new factory in [[Pontedera]], culminating in the four-engine [[Piaggio P.108]] bomber.\n\nRinaldo died in 1938, by which time Piaggio was owned by multiple shareholders within the family, along with the entrepreneur [[:it:Attilio Odero|Attilio Odero]]. Management of the company passed to his sons [[Enrico Piaggio|Enrico]] and Armando.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.referenceforbusiness.com/history2/83/Piaggio-C-S-p-A.html |title = History of Piaggio & C. S.p.A.}}</ref>\n\nBy 1940 Piaggio was manufacturing trains, [[nautical]] fittings, [[aircraft engine]]s, aeroplanes, trucks, trams, buses, [[funicular]]s and aluminium windows and doors. The [[Pontedera]] plant was destroyed by Allied bombing and production activities were relocated to the [[Biella]] area. After the war, Enrico Piaggio decided to diversify the company's activities outside the aeronautical industry to address a perceived need for a modern, affordable mode of transport for the Italian mass market. The first attempt, based on a small [[motorcycle]] made for [[Parachuting|parachutists]], was known as the MP5 and nicknamed the \"[[Paperino]]\" (the Italian name for [[Donald Duck]]) because of its strange shape. Ultimately Enrico Piaggio did not like it and asked [[Corradino D'Ascanio]] to redesign it.\n\nD'Ascanio, an aeronautical engineer responsible for the design and construction of the first modern helicopter by [[Agusta]], was not naturally enthusiastic about [[motorcycle]]s, judging them to be uncomfortable and bulky, with wheels that were difficult to change after a puncture. When asked to design a motorcycle for [[Ferdinando Innocenti]], D'Ascanio had come up with a step through scooter design but D'Ascanio and Innocenti disagreed over use of pressings rather than tubing so D'Ascanio brought his design to Piaggio. Innocenti would ultimately use D'Ascanio's original design for their [[Lambretta]] scooter.\n\nPiaggio asked D'Ascanio to create a simple, robust and affordable vehicle. The [[motorcycle]] had to be easy to drive for both men and women, be able to carry a passenger, and not get its driver's clothes dirty. The engineer's drawings proved a significant departure from the Paperino. With the help of [[Mario D'Este]] he prepared the first Vespa project, manufactured at Piaggio newly-rebuilt Pontedera headquarters in April 1946. Piaggio launched the [[Vespa]] (Italian for \"wasp\") and within ten years more than a million units had been produced. The Italian language gained a new word, \"vespare\", meaning to go somewhere on a Vespa.<ref>{{cite web |url = https://ultimatemotorcycling.com/2010/08/29/piaggio-origins-and-vespa-history/ |title = Piaggio Origins & Vespa History}}</ref>\n\n===Ownership===\n[[File:Vespa a Todi.JPG|thumbnail|[[Vespa]] in a Todi street]]\nVespa thrived until 1992 when [[Gianni Agnelli]] became CEO. Agnelli was already suffering from cancer and died in 2003. In 1999 [[Morgan Grenfell Private Equity]] acquired Piaggio, but hopes for a quick sale were dashed by a failed joint venture in China.{{Clarify|date=February 2013}} In Italy, Piaggio invested 15 million euros ($19.4&nbsp;million) in a new motorcycle but dropped it after building a prototype. By the end of 2002, the company had run up 577&nbsp;million Euros in debt on revenues of 945&nbsp;million Euros, and booked a loss of 129&nbsp;million Euros.\n\nIn 2003 Piaggio's debt was reduced a 100 million Euro investment made by [[:it:IMMSI|IMMSI]], a holding company of the Colaninno family. 150&nbsp;million shares were also converted by creditor banks. Reflecting on his investment, [[:it:Roberto Colaninno|Roberto Colaninno]] said,\n\n\"A lot of people told me I was crazy. Piaggio wasn't dying. It just needed to be treated better.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB114947493428871213|title=Vespa's Builder Scoots Back To Profitability}}</ref>\"\n\n[[Roberto Colaninno|Colannino]] became the new chairman of Piaggio, while Dr. Rocco Sabelli becoming the managing director. Sabelli redesigned the production line according to Japanese principles so that every Piaggio scooter could be made on any assembly line. Contrary to expectations, Mr. Colaninno did not fire a single worker \u2013 a move which helped seduce the company's skeptical unions. \"Everyone in a company is part of the value chain,\" said Colaninno. All bonuses for blue-collar workers and management were based on the same criteria: profit margins and customer satisfaction. Air conditioning was installed in the factory for the first time, increasing productivity. He also gave the company's engineers, who had been idled by the company's financial crisis, deadlines for projects. They rolled out two world firsts in 2004: a gas-electric hybrid scooter and a sophisticated tilting scooter with two wheels in front and one in back to grip the road better.\n\nOne of Piaggio's problems Mr. Colaninno couldn't fix from the inside was its scale. Even though Piaggio was the European market leader, it was dwarfed by rivals [[Honda]] and [[Yamaha Motor Company|Yamaha]]. A year after restoring Piaggio's health, Colaninno directed Piaggio's takeover of the Italian scooter and motorcycle manufacturer [[Aprilia]], and with it the Aprilia-owned [[Moto Guzzi]], a storied Italian manufacturer of motorcycles.\n\nIn 2006, Piaggio floated on the [[Milan Stock Exchange]], becoming a public company.\n\n===Production Development===\nIn 1956, with production of the millionth [[Vespa]] scooter, Italy had its first mass-produced motorised vehicle. Taking advantage of increased cash flow thanks to the success of the Vespa, Piaggio developed other products, including the 1957 [[Vespa 400]], a compact passenger car.\n\nIn 1959 Piaggio came under the control of the [[Agnelli family]], the owners of car maker [[Fiat|Fiat SpA]].\n\nBy 1960 Vespa had produced and sold 4 million units worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|language = en|url = http://www.museopiaggio.it/en/history/|title = Piaggio History}}</ref>\n\nIn 1964 the aeronautical and motorcycle divisions of Piaggio split to become two independent companies as a result of the wide ownership by Fiat in Italian industry.{{Clarify|date=February 2013}} The aeronautical division was named IAM Rinaldo Piaggio. The aircraft company [[Piaggio Aero]] was controlled by the family of Piero Ferrari, who still hold 10% of [[Ferrari]].\n\nIn 1969 Piaggio purchased the motorcycle company [[Gilera]], one of the oldest European motorcycle manufacturers (founded in 1909), famous for its sporting achievements and world titles in the [[Motocycle World Championship|Motorcycle World Championship]].<ref>{{cite web|language = en|url = https://www.autoevolution.com/moto/gilera/|title = Gilera \u2013 Models and History}}</ref>\n\nIn 1971 a steering wheel was added to the [[Piaggio Ape]], a model first produced in 1948, culminating in the Ape Car. Four years later, in 1975, the company made the first prototype of an electric Ape.<ref>{{cite web|language = en|url = http://www.tukxi.com/history.html|title = History of Piaggio Ape}}</ref>\n\nIn 1988 the Vespa reached the milestone of 10 million units produced.<ref>{{cite web|language = en|url = https://www.mirror.co.uk/lifestyle/motoring/happy-days-vespa-celebrates-70th-7850941|title = Happy Days! Vespa celebrates its 70th birthday}}</ref>\n\nIn 1996, on the fiftieth anniversary of the first model, [[Vespa]] passed 15 million units produced and the new 4-stroke Vespa ET, the first completely new Vespa for 18 years, was launched.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vespa.com/en_EN/Heritage.html|title=Vespa History}}</ref> Piaggio was still in poor financial health but its brand recognition remained strong, boosted by the appearance of the ET4 in several Hollywood films.\n\nIn 1999, in [[Baramati]], production began on a three-wheeler Ape for the [[India]]n domestic market.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.motoroids.com/news/piaggio-inaugurates-vespa-manufacturing-plant-in-baramati/|title=Piaggio inaugurates Vespa manufacturing plant in Baramati}}</ref>\n\nIn 2000 Piaggio and Vespa returned to the United States with the opening of the first Vespa Boutique in Los Angeles. In that same year the Piaggio Historical Museum was inaugurated in [[Pontedera]]. The museum showcases the Piaggio Historical Archive, one of the most comprehensive company archives on the industrial history of Italy.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.museopiaggio.it/en/|title=Piaggio Museum}}</ref>\n\nIn 2001 the Piaggio Group acquired Derbi-Nacional Motor SA,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.piaggiogroup.com/en/group/brands/derbi|title=Derbi}}</ref> an historical Spanish brand founded in 1922 that had won 18 world titles and was a continental leader in the small displacement motorbike segment. In the same year [[Gilera]] returned to the [[Motorcycle World Championship]] and immediately won the world title in the 125 category with Manuel Poggiali.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.motogp.com/en/news/2001/05/21/poggiali-brings-gilera-first-125-win-for-45-years/130710|title=Poggiali brings Gilera first 125 win for 45 years}}</ref>\n\nIn 2004, at the end of December, the final contract for the acquisition of the [[Aprilia]]-[[Moto Guzzi Group]] was signed. The most important European two-wheeler group is born.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.webbikeworld.com/motorcycle-news/piaggio-aprilia.htm|title=Piaggio Buys Aprilia & Moto Guzzi}}</ref>\n\nIn 2007 Piaggio Group officially arrives in [[Vietnam]]. The Vinh Puch plant includes R&D, welding and painting activities, as well as final assembly of the scooters, with warehouse, testing, quality control and office areas.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.piaggiogroup.com/en/archive/press/piaggio-group-official-opening-new-vietnam-factory|title=Piaggio Group: official opening of new Vietnam factory}}</ref>\n\nIn 2009 the Piaggio Mp3 Hybrid makes its debut on the market which was first hybrid scooter in the world, integrating the conventional low-environmental-impact internal combustion engine with a zero-emission electric motor and combining the advantages of the two power trains.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.autoblog.com/2010/07/07/piaggio-launches-mp3-hybrid-300ie-scooter/|title=Piaggio launches MP3 Hybrid 300ie scooter}}</ref>\n\nIn [[Baramati]] (State of [[Maharashtra]]), in 2012, the Piaggio Group's new plant for the production of Vespa's for the local market was opened.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.piaggiogroup.com/en/archive/press/piaggio-group-vespa-makes-its-official-debut-indian-market|title=Piaggio Group: Vespa makes its official debut on the Indian market}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013 the PADC \u2013 Piaggio Advanced Design Center opened in [[Pasadena]] (California, United States).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cycleworld.com/2012/04/17/will-the-motorcycle-of-the-future-come-from-pasadena|title=Will The Motorcycle of the Future Come From Pasadena?}}</ref> The Vespa 946 was also launched this year, along with the new Vespa Primavera, the latest evolution of the \"small body\" family.\n\nIn 2013 Vespa's worldwide sales numbered almost 190,000 units; in 2004 the figure stood at 58,000. In ten years of continuous progression over 1.3&nbsp;million new Vespas have reached the streets of the world. Since 1946 over 18 million Vespas have been produced and sold.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.news18.com/news/auto/70-years-of-vespa-all-the-vespas-produced-ever-1233703.html|title=70 Years of Vespa: All the Vespas Produced, Ever}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2017 Foton and Piaggio agreed to form a joint venture to develop and produce light commercial vehicle.<ref>[http://www.piaggiocommercialvehicles.com/it_IT/news-list/partnership-piaggio-foton/ Piaggio and Foton joint venture]</ref> Based on Foton chassis the new vehicle was sold by [[Piaggio Commercial Vehicle]] division in Europe and in all markets around the world but not in China. The vehicle is intended to be a successor of the [[Piaggio Porter]] and production is planned to start in mid-2019 in [[Pontedera]] ([[Italy]]) with all components produced by Foton in China.<ref>[http://www.repubblica.it/economia/finanza/2018/04/16/news/piaggio_all_accordo_con_i_cinesi_di_foton-194028229/ Piaggio Accordo con Foton per il nuovo Porter]</ref>\n\n== \"Cultural Project\" Piaggio ==\nPiaggio's \"cultural project\" promotes the reconstruction and enhancement of the company's heritage and is composed by three initiatives:  the Piaggio Foundation, the Historical Archives and the Piaggio Museum. In 2003 the Museum and Archives were recognised as the Best Corporate Museum and Archive by winning the Italian prize \"Premio Impresa e Cultura\".<ref>[http://www.piaggiogroup.com/en/node/4531]{{dead link|date=February 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\nIn 2016, under the patronage of the [[Ministry of Cultural Heritage and Activities and Tourism (Italy)|Italian Ministry of Culture]], Piaggio received the [[Corporate Art Awards|Corporate Art Award]] from [[pptArt]] for its Corporate Museum.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pptart.net/winners|title=2016 Corporate Art Awards - Corporate winners}}</ref>\n\n==Brands and models==\n[[File:Light blue Vespa GL, front.jpg|thumb|upright|1962 Vespa 150 GL]]\n[[File:Piaggio mp3.jpg|thumb|Piaggio MP3 three-wheel scooter]]\n\n===Group brands===\n* [[Aprilia]] \u2013 motorcycles, [[scooter (motorcycle)|scooter]] and [[moped]]s\n* Piaggio \u2013 scooters, mopeds.\n* [[Vespa]] \u2013 scooters and mopeds\n* [[Scarabeo]] \u2013 scooters and mopeds\n* [[Derbi]] \u2013 motorcycles, scooters, mopeds and recreational [[All-terrain vehicle|ATV]]s (''quads'')\n* [[Gilera]] \u2013 motorcycles, scooters, mopeds and recreational [[All-terrain vehicle|ATV]]s (''quads'')\n* [[Moto Guzzi]] \u2013 motorcycles\n* [[Piaggio Commercial Vehicles]] \u2013  [[light commercial vehicle]]s\n\n===Models===\n[[File:Piaggio Grillo a Rovigo.jpg|thumb|[[Piaggio Grillo]].]]\n* Piaggio 110 Bicycle bodywork(110 anniversaries)\n* [[Piaggio Ape|Ape]] \u2013 3-wheel micro [[light commercial vehicle]]s\n* [[Piaggio Porter]] 4-wheel [[microvan]]s and micro-[[pickup truck|pickup]]s, same as a [[Daihatsu Hijet]].\n* [[Piaggio Quargo]] 4-wheel [[microvan]]s and micro-[[pickup truck|pickup]]s,\n* [[Piaggio MP3]] tilting 3-wheel scooter\n* Diesis 50/100 (50cc air-cooled [[2-stroke]] and 100&nbsp;cc water-cooled 2-stroke) made between 2001 and 2005\n* FLY50/100/125/150\n* Free50\n* Typhoon 50&nbsp;cc, 80&nbsp;cc, 125&nbsp;cc (1995\u20132000;2012)\n* Sfera NSL (50&nbsp;cc & 80&nbsp;cc) 1991\u20131995\n* Sfera RST (RST standing for Restyle) (50&nbsp;cc 2-stroke & 125&nbsp;cc 4-stroke) 1995 \u2013 ??\n* [[Piaggio NRG|NRG mc1-3]] (50&nbsp;cc) (mc standing for mark.)\n* NRG Power PureJet (50&nbsp;cc fuel injection, water cooling)\n* NRG Power DT (air-cooled) and DD (liquid-cooled), both introduced in 2005\n* NTT (water-cooled 2-stroke) made between 1995 and 1998\n* Liberty (50&nbsp;cc 2-stroke, 125&nbsp; cc & 150&nbsp;cc Quattrotempi)\n* Liberty S (50&nbsp;cc 125&nbsp;cc 200&nbsp;cc)\n* LT ( US models of the Liberty. 50&nbsp;cc and 125&nbsp;cc 2-stroke)\n* Skipper ST (125&nbsp;cc)\n* [[Piaggio Ciao]] (50&nbsp;cc)\n* Si (50&nbsp;cc)\n* Superbravo (50&nbsp;cc)\n* Avanti (50&nbsp;cc)\n* Grillo (50&nbsp;cc)\n* Bravo (50&nbsp;cc)\n* Grande (50&nbsp;cc)\n* Boxer (50&nbsp;cc)\n* Boxer 2 (50&nbsp;cc)\n* [[Piaggio X7|X7]] 125 (European market), 250\n* [[Piaggio X7 Evo|X7 Evo]] (125, 300&nbsp;cc) \u2013 announced 2009\n* [[Piaggio X8|X8]] 125 (European market), 250, 400\n* [[Piaggio Xevo|XEvo]] 125, 250, 400\n* X9 125/250 cc Evolution \u2013 the Evolution models superseded the previous X9 models in 2004, which were fitted with Honda engines\n* X9 500 cc Evolution with features not fitted on 125/250 cc models: hydraulic centre stand, integrated rider-to-pillion communication system, mobile-phone charger in front dash cubbyhole\n* BV200/250\n* BV350\n* BV500 \u2013 neo-classic style, automatic transmission, top-speed 100&nbsp;mph\n* [[Piaggio Beverly|Beverly]] (125&nbsp;cc; 250&nbsp;cc; 400&nbsp;cc; 500&nbsp;cc: Beverly is the Italian name for the BV models)\n* Medley 125&nbsp;cc, Medley S 125cc\n* Carnaby (125&nbsp;cc & 200&nbsp;cc)\n* Free 50 (50&nbsp;cc)\n* Hexagon (125&nbsp;cc; 150&nbsp;cc; 180&nbsp;cc; 250&nbsp;cc)\n* T (125&nbsp;cc; 150&nbsp;cc)\n* Piaggio Velofax or Vespino 1995 to 1999.\n* Quartz (50&nbsp;cc 2-stroke, liquid-cooled)\n* Quartz (125 cc, 2-stroke, air-cooled)\n* Storm (125 cc, 4-stroke, air-cooled)\n* M500 (505 cc, 2-stroke, microcar)\n* Ravi Piaggio Strom (125&nbsp;cc, 4-stroke) Joint venture of Piaggio with Ravi and available in Pakistani market\n* [[Piaggio Ape|Piaggio Ape RR]]\n* [[Piaggio Zip|Zip]] 50&nbsp;cc 2-stroke, air-cooled (pre 2000)\n* [[Piaggio Zip|Zip SP]] 50&nbsp;cc 2-stroke, water-cooled (pre 2000)\n* [[Piaggio Zip|Zip (Cat)]] 50&nbsp;cc 2-stroke, air-cooled (2000 onwards)\n* [[Piaggio Zip|Zip SP]] 50&nbsp;cc two-stroke, water-cooled (2000 onwards)\n* [[Piaggio Zip|Zip 4t]] 50&nbsp;cc 4-stroke, air-cooled\n* [[Piaggio Zip|Zip 4t 100]] 96.2&nbsp;cc 4-stroke, air-cooled\n* [[Piaggio Zip|Zip 125]] 125&nbsp;cc 4-stroke, air-cooled\n{{Expand list|date=August 2008}}\n\n===Electric scooters===\nThe new [[plug-in hybrid]] version of the [[Piaggio MP3]] will be equipped with a 125&nbsp;cc petrol engine and electric motor, which offers about {{convert|141|mpgus|abbr=on}} and travels {{convert|13|mi}} using battery power alone. This machine could be out in 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.treehugger.com/files/2008/11/piaggio-scooter.php |title=Piaggio Scooters Gone Green: 141 MPG Hybrid |publisher=TreeHugger |date= |accessdate=2009-08-10}}</ref>\n\nPiaggio/Vespa are also developing hybrid electric scooters. There are two models in the works, based on the popular [[Vespa LX 50]] and the beefier [[Piaggio X8]] 125.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.treehugger.com/files/2006/04/vespa_unveils_h.php#ch01 |title=Vespa Unveils Hybrid Scooters |publisher=TreeHugger |date= |accessdate=2009-08-10}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}<!--added above External links/Sources by script-assisted edit-->\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|Italy|Companies}}\n{{stack begin}}{{Commons category|Piaggio}}{{stack end}}\n* [http://www.piaggiogroup.com Piaggio official website]\n* [http://www.piaggiocommercialvehicles.com/ Piaggio Commercial Vehicles]\n* [https://www.museopiaggio.it/en/ Piaggio Museum - Museo Piaggio]\n{{Gilera}}\n{{Moto Guzzi}}\n{{Aprilia motorcycles}}\n{{Automotive industry in Italy}}\n{{Major Italian motorcycle manufacturers}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Italian brands]]\n[[Category:Vehicle manufacturing companies established in 1884]]\n[[Category:1884 establishments in Italy]]\n[[Category:Piaggio Group| ]]\n[[Category:Companies listed on the Borsa Italiana]]\n[[Category:Motorcycle manufacturers of Italy]]\n[[Category:Aircraft manufacturers of Italy]]\n[[Category:Aircraft engine manufacturers of Italy]]\n[[Category:Scooter manufacturers]]\n[[Category:Moped manufacturers]]\n[[Category:Plug-in hybrid vehicles]]\n[[Category:Private equity portfolio companies]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Tuscany]]\n", "name_user": "Fabio Roffinott", "label": "safe", "comment": "/change on commission/ I've changed the infobox company data with the new financial data", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Piaggio"}
{"title_page": "Timeline of the 2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States", "text_new": "{{short description|Timeline of ongoing pandemic in the United States}}\n{{use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\nThe following is a timeline of the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States|2020 coronavirus pandemic]] in the United States.\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/United States medical cases chart}}\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/United States cases by state}}\n\n==Timeline==\n===January===\n{{See also|2020 coronavirus pandemic in California#January|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Washington (state)#January}}\nThe [[Centers for Disease Control and Prevention]] dispatched public health experts to screen incoming airport passengers at John F. Kennedy International Airport in New York, San Francisco, and Los Angeles beginning in January 17 and adding monitors at Chicago and Atlanta after the second US case was confirmed in Chicago<ref>Santhanam, Laura. (24 January 2020). \"CDC confirms 2nd U.S. case of novel coronavirus in Chicago\". [https://www.pbs.org/newshour/health/cdc-confirms-second-u-s-case-of-novel-coronavirus-in-chicago PBS website] Retrieved 2 April 2020.</ref> The first reported case in the U.S. is in [[Washington (state)|Washington state]] on January 21, 2020, which affects a man who had returned from [[Wuhan]], China. He is released after two weeks of treatment. A few days later, another case is reported in Chicago, by a woman who had also just returned from Wuhan.<ref>[https://wgntv.com/news/chicago-woman-infects-husband-with-coronavirus-first-human-to-human-spread-in-us/ \"Chicago woman infects husband with coronavirus, US issues travel warning\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312130121/https://wgntv.com/news/chicago-woman-infects-husband-with-coronavirus-first-human-to-human-spread-in-us/ |date=March 12, 2020 }}, WGN9 TV, Chicago, IL. January 30, 2020</ref> A third case is confirmed a day later in [[Orange County, California|Orange County]], California.<ref>[https://www.ocregister.com/2020/02/04/risk-of-catching-coronavirus-in-so-cal-is-low-health-officials-say/ \"Orange County coronavirus patient released, in good condition, health officials say\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200205195530/https://www.ocregister.com/2020/02/04/risk-of-catching-coronavirus-in-so-cal-is-low-health-officials-say/ |date=February 5, 2020 }}, ''Orange County Register'', February 4, 2020</ref> Two more cases are confirmed on January 26, similarly by two people who had returned from Wuhan.<ref>[https://losangeles.cbslocal.com/2020/01/26/public-health-officials-confirm-first-case-of-novel-coronavirus-in-la-county/ \"Public Health Officials Confirm First Case Of Novel Coronavirus In LA County\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200126192042/https://losangeles.cbslocal.com/2020/01/26/public-health-officials-confirm-first-case-of-novel-coronavirus-in-la-county/ |date=January 26, 2020 }}, KCAL TV, January 26, 2020</ref> All cases to this point are allowed to self-isolate at home for two weeks, after which time they are assumed to be- no longer infected.\n\nThe U.S. government evacuates 195 State Department employees from Wuhan along with their families and other U.S. citizens to [[March Air Reserve Base]] near [[Riverside, California]] on January 29, where they are kept under quarantine for 14 days, although none had been infected.<ref>[https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-usa/two-planes-left-wuhan-china-en-route-to-us-state-department-idUSKBN20105M \"Two more U.S. evacuation planes leave coronavirus epicenter Wuhan\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200216045906/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-usa/two-planes-left-wuhan-china-en-route-to-us-state-department-idUSKBN20105M |date=February 16, 2020 }}, Reuters, February 6, 2020</ref><ref>[https://timesofsandiego.com/tech/2020/02/10/with-no-signs-of-infection-coronavirus-evacuees-in-riverside-set-to-end-quarantine/ With No Signs of Infection, Coronavirus Evacuees in Riverside Set to End Quarantine]{{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312130817/https://timesofsandiego.com/tech/2020/02/10/with-no-signs-of-infection-coronavirus-evacuees-in-riverside-set-to-end-quarantine/ |date=March 12, 2020 }}, Times of San Diego, February 10, 2020</ref> On January 30, the first case of person-to-person transmission is confirmed in Chicago, between a married couple, after the wife returned from China.<ref name=\"Marketwatch\">[https://www.marketwatch.com/story/coronavirus-update-a-new-task-force-195-us-citizens-in-isolation-and-who-to-decide-if-its-a-public-health-emergency-2020-01-30 \"First U.S. case of person-to-person transmission confirmed, 195 U.S. citizens in isolation and WHO declares a public health emergency\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130221503/https://www.marketwatch.com/story/coronavirus-update-a-new-task-force-195-us-citizens-in-isolation-and-who-to-decide-if-its-a-public-health-emergency-2020-01-30 |date=January 30, 2020 }}, ''MarketWatch'', January 30, 2010</ref> On the same day, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) names the coronavirus outbreak that originated in Wuhan, China, a public health emergency of international concern.<ref name=Marketwatch/>\n\n[[File:Donald Trump Coronavirus briefing.jpg|thumb|President [[Donald Trump]] received a briefing on the coronavirus in China, January 2020|alt=]]\nThe following day, another case of a person who returned from Wuhan is confirmed in California, which marks the seventh known case in the U.S.<ref>[https://www.cnbc.com/2020/01/31/california-and-cdc-officials-confirm-7th-case-of-coronavirus-in-the-us.html \"CDC officials confirm 7th US case of coronavirus, in California man who traveled to China\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201021201/https://www.cnbc.com/2020/01/31/california-and-cdc-officials-confirm-7th-case-of-coronavirus-in-the-us.html |date=February 1, 2020 }}, CNBC, January 31, 2020</ref> That is followed by the U.S. [[Department of Health and Human Services]] declaring a public health emergency, and imposing a mandatory 14-day [[quarantine]] for any U.S. citizens who has visited Hubei Province within the preceding two weeks. It also begins denying entry of non-U.S. nationals who have traveled to China within the preceding two weeks. This is the first such travel restriction by the U.S. in more than 50 years,<ref>[https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-k-reports-first-coronavirus-cases-as-china-allies-limit-ties-11580467046 \"U.S. Imposes Entry Restrictions Over Coronavirus\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201022426/https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-k-reports-first-coronavirus-cases-as-china-allies-limit-ties-11580467046 |date=February 1, 2020 }}, ''Wall Street Journal'', January 31, 2020</ref> and is soon followed by Australia and Japan imposing similar travel restrictions.<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/01/world/asia/china-coronavirus-us-australia.html \"China Increasingly Walled Off as Countries Seek to Stem Coronavirus\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200204225148/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/01/world/asia/china-coronavirus-us-australia.html |date=February 4, 2020 }}, ''New York Times'', February 1, 2020</ref>\n\n===February===\n{{See also|2020 coronavirus pandemic in California#February|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Massachusetts#February|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Washington (state)#February}}\n\n[[File:Senior DOD Official Holds News Conference feb 3 2020 DOD 107640372-1280x720-2765k-5e6fb7fa80e93.webm|thumb|start=01:37|A senior DOD official holds a news conference at [[the Pentagon]] on February 3]]\n[[File:White House Press Briefing (49591617778).jpg|thumb|Members of the Coronavirus Task Force hold a press briefing at the White House on February 26]]\nNew cases are being reported throughout the country nearly every day. Many are people who have recently returned from China, including a college student from Boston and a woman in California who returned from Wuhan.<ref name=\"uk.reuters.com\">{{Cite web|url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-china-health-usa-california-idUKKBN1ZX01P|title=Ninth case of fast-moving coronavirus confirmed in U.S.|date=February 2, 2020|work=[[Reuters]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200203011127/https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-china-health-usa-california-idUKKBN1ZX01P|archive-date=February 3, 2020|access-date=February 3, 2020}}</ref> Two more cases of person-to-person transmission are reported in California.\n\nOn February 5, the twelfth case is discovered: another college student from Wisconsin.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://edition.cnn.com/asia/live-news/coronavirus-outbreak-02-05-20-intl-hnk/index.html|title=Wisconsin coronavirus patient is isolated at home|last=Lin Erdman|first=Shelby|date=5 February 2020|website=CNN.com|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206030623/https://edition.cnn.com/asia/live-news/coronavirus-outbreak-02-05-20-intl-hnk/index.html|archive-date=February 6, 2020|access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref> That day, the U.S. evacuates 345 citizens from Hubei Province and takes them to two air bases in California to be quarantined for 14 days.<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/05/us/coronavirus-flights-wuhan.html  \"Hundreds of Americans Were Evacuated From the Coronavirus Epicenter. Now Comes the Wait.\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206130218/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/05/us/coronavirus-flights-wuhan.html |date=February 6, 2020 }}, \u2018\u2019New York Times\u2019\u2019, February 5, 2020</ref> Another government evacuation flight takes place on February 6, containing 300 passengers, most of who are taken to bases in Nebraska and Texas.  By this time, more than 500 people are quarantined at three air bases.<ref>[https://q13fox.com/2020/02/06/planeloads-of-americans-flee-growing-coronavirus-outbreak-in-wuhan-as-12th-case-is-reported-in-the-us/ \"Planeloads of Americans flee growing coronavirus outbreak in Wuhan as 12th case is reported in the US\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200208142723/https://q13fox.com/2020/02/06/planeloads-of-americans-flee-growing-coronavirus-outbreak-in-wuhan-as-12th-case-is-reported-in-the-us/ |date=February 8, 2020 }}, ''Q13Fox'', February 6, 2020</ref> On February 6, the [[Centers for Disease Control]] began sending 90 of its own viral detection tests to state-run labs which discovered the tests were inadequate and viral samples had to be shipped to the Atlanta CDC lab instead.<ref>Yasmeen Abutaleb, Josh Dawsey, Ellen Nakashima and Greg Miller. (4 April 2020). \"The U.S. was beset by denial and dysfunction as the coronavirus raged\". [https://www.washingtonpost.com/national-security/2020/04/04/coronavirus-government-dysfunction/?arc404=true Washington Post website] Retrieved 5 April 2020.</ref>  From February 12 to 15, three more cases are confirmed, all who travelled from Wuhan, and are similarly quarantined.<ref>[https://www.kcra.com/article/2nd-case-new-coronavirus-confirmed-among-china-evacuees/30902073# \"2nd evacuee from China tests positive for coronavirus\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200213014119/https://www.kcra.com/article/2nd-case-new-coronavirus-confirmed-among-china-evacuees/30902073 |date=February 13, 2020 }}, KCRA, February 12, 2020</ref><ref>[https://www.cbs8.com/article/news/health/coronavirus/1-of-2-patients-released-from-isolation-at-uc-san-diego-health-after-recovering-from-covid-19/509-e3bcfa0c-3c5b-4519-b210-e1f072ae353a \"1 of 2 patients released from isolation at UC San Diego Health after recovering from COVID-19\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200222104915/https://www.cbs8.com/article/news/health/coronavirus/1-of-2-patients-released-from-isolation-at-uc-san-diego-health-after-recovering-from-covid-19/509-e3bcfa0c-3c5b-4519-b210-e1f072ae353a |date=February 22, 2020 }}, ''CBS8'', February 19, 2020</ref>\n\nOn February 15, the government evacuates 338 U.S. nationals stranded aboard the cruise ship [[Diamond Princess (ship)|''Diamond Princess'']], which had been held in quarantine in [[Yokohama, Japan]].<ref>[https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-51514102 \"Coronavirus: US to evacuate citizens from Diamond Princess\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200216050642/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-51514102 |date=February 16, 2020 }}, ''BBC'', February 15, 2020</ref> Fourteen of those repatriated people are infected with the virus.<ref>[https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-japan-cruiseship-usa/u-s-state-dept-says-fourteen-test-positive-for-coronavirus-from-cruise-ship-in-japan-idUSKBN20B0U9 \"U.S. flies 338 Americans home from cruise ship, including 14 with coronavirus\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200217112803/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-japan-cruiseship-usa/u-s-state-dept-says-fourteen-test-positive-for-coronavirus-from-cruise-ship-in-japan-idUSKBN20B0U9 |date=February 17, 2020 }}, Reuters, February 17, 2020</ref> Five more nationals who were also reported as being infected are evacuated from the ship the following week, and are quarantined at an airbase in California. Six more cases are subsequently confirmed among those who were evacuated from the cruise ship.<ref>[https://edition.cnn.com/2020/02/17/health/evacuated-passengers-test-positive-coronavirus/index.html \"13 Americans moved to Omaha facility from evacuation flights, US officials say\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200218210337/https://edition.cnn.com/2020/02/17/health/evacuated-passengers-test-positive-coronavirus/index.html |date=February 18, 2020 }}, CNN, February 18, 2020</ref>\n\nOn February 20 and 21, two more cases of people who had returned from China are confirmed in California.<ref>[https://www.latimes.com/california/story/2020-02-21/coronavirus-humboldt-sacramento-county-total-california-cases-to-15 \"California's coronavirus cases now at 15, with new diagnoses in Humboldt, Sacramento areas\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200222020122/https://www.latimes.com/california/story/2020-02-21/coronavirus-humboldt-sacramento-county-total-california-cases-to-15 |date=February 22, 2020 }}, ''Los Angeles Times'', February 21, 2020</ref> The first case of [[community transmission]], because it had no known origin, is confirmed in Solano County, California, on February 26.<ref>[https://www.cdph.ca.gov/Programs/OPA/Pages/NR20-006.aspx \"CDC Confirms Possible First Instance of COVID-19 Community Transmission in California\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228203724/https://www.cdph.ca.gov/Programs/OPA/Pages/NR20-006.aspx |date=February 28, 2020 }}, ''Calif. Dept. of Public Health'', February 26, 2020</ref> A second case of unknown origin is confirmed two days later, also in California, followed by others in Oregon and Washington state.<ref>[https://www.cnn.com/2020/02/28/health/coronavirus-us-updates-california-patient/index.html \"New coronavirus cases in California and Oregon are second and third of unknown origin in US\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229001102/https://www.cnn.com/2020/02/28/health/coronavirus-us-updates-california-patient/index.html |date=February 29, 2020 }}, CNN, February 28, 2020</ref>\n\nOn February 29, the first death from coronavirus in the U.S. is reported at EvergreenHealth Medical Center in [[Kirkland, Washington]], followed by two other confirmed cases, those in a nursing home in the same city.<ref>[https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/1st-coronavirus-death-u-s-officials-say-n1145931 \"Washington state man becomes first U.S. death from coronavirus\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229192416/https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/1st-coronavirus-death-u-s-officials-say-n1145931 |date=February 29, 2020 }}, NBC News, February 29, 2020</ref> New cases continue to show up in California and Illinois.<ref>[https://www.rollcall.com/2020/02/29/coronavirus-response-efforts-ramp-up-as-first-u-s-death-confirmed/ \"Coronavirus response efforts ramp up as first US death confirmed\"], ''Roll Call'', February 29, 2020</ref>\n\n===March===\n{{See also|2020 coronavirus pandemic in California#March|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Massachusetts#March|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Minnesota#March|2020 coronavirus pandemic in New York (state)|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Washington (state)#March|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Illinois}}\n\n====March 1\u20132====\n[[File:Coronavirus Task Force Meeting (49615398926).jpg|thumb|Vice President [[Mike Pence]] meets with White House coronavirus task force principals on March 2 in the [[White House Situation Room]].]]\nIn New York, Governor [[Andrew Cuomo]] announces the state's first reported case of COVID-19: a woman in her late 30s, who apparently contracted the virus while traveling in Iran and is self-isolating at home, in New York City.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://mobile.twitter.com/BNODesk/status/1234280201825193986 |title=Twitter |publisher=Twitter}}</ref> Oregon confirmed its second case, a household contact of its first case.<ref name=\"oregon.2.1\">{{Cite web |url=https://content.govdelivery.com/accounts/ORDHS/bulletins/27ea91b |title=Second Positive Case of COVID-19 Appears in Oregon |website=The Oregon Health Authority and Department of Human Services |access-date=March 2, 2020}}</ref> The [[Rhode Island Department of Health]] announces a presumptive case in a person in their 40s who had traveled to Italy in mid-February,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ri.gov/press/view/37818 |title=First Presumptive Positive Case of COVID-19 Identified at RIDOH's State Health Laboratories |date=March 1, 2020 |website=RI.gov |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200301172041/https://www.ri.gov/press/view/37818 |archive-date=March 1, 2020}}</ref> and a second case, a teenager who had traveled with the first person.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.pressherald.com/2020/03/01/first-virus-case-confirmed-in-rhode-island/ |title=2 cases of COVID-19 virus confirmed in Rhode Island |date=March 1, 2020 |website=Press Herald |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302014934/https://www.pressherald.com/2020/03/01/first-virus-case-confirmed-in-rhode-island/ |archive-date=March 2, 2020 |agency=Associated Press}}</ref>\n\nOn March 2, coronavirus cases in the U.S. reach 100, including repatriated citizens from Wuhan or the ''Diamond Princess''.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.cnn.com/asia/live-news/coronavirus-outbreak-03-02-20-intl-hnk/h_ab394740b4249012dc266df09451872f |title=There are now 100 cases of coronavirus in the US |date=March 2, 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302221314/https://www.cnn.com/asia/live-news/coronavirus-outbreak-03-02-20-intl-hnk/h_ab394740b4249012dc266df09451872f |archive-date=March 2, 2020 |publisher=CNN}}</ref> [[New Hampshire]] officials announce the state's first case, an employee with [[Dartmouth\u2013Hitchcock Medical Center]] who had been to Italy.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nbcboston.com/news/local/1st-confirmed-case-of-coronavirus-in-nh/2084452/ |title=1st Confirmed Case of Coronavirus in NH |website=NBC Boston |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303123944/https://www.nbcboston.com/news/local/1st-confirmed-case-of-coronavirus-in-nh/2084452/ |archive-date=March 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n====March 3\u20134====\nOn March 3, when the state has no confirmed cases, Ohio Governor [[Mike DeWine]] cancels the [[Arnold Sports Festival|Arnold Classic]] due to coronavirus concerns, a move which the ''Washington Post'' said seemed radical at the time.<ref name=\":8:\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/coronavirus-ohio-dewine-outbreak/2020/03/16/9bde6b1e-67b2-11ea-9923-57073adce27c_story.html |title=Ohio Gov. Mike DeWine's coronavirus response has become a national guide to the crisis |last=Witte |first=Griff |last2=Zezima |first2=Katie |date=16 March 2020 |website=[[Washington Post]] |url-status=live |access-date=17 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317142655/https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/coronavirus-ohio-dewine-outbreak/2020/03/16/9bde6b1e-67b2-11ea-9923-57073adce27c_story.html |archive-date=March 17, 2020 }}</ref> On March 3, [[Arizona]]'s Department of Health Services reports a new confirmed case in Maricopa County, a man in his 20s who had made contact with a case outside of Arizona. The man is isolated in his home.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.abc15.com/news/region-phoenix-metro/central-phoenix/coronavirus-in-arizona-officials-confirm-new-presumptive-positive-case |title=Coronavirus in Arizona: Officials confirm new 'presumptive positive' case in Maricopa County |date=March 3, 2020 |publisher=[[KNXV-TV|ABC 15 Arizona]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304001348/https://www.abc15.com/news/region-phoenix-metro/central-phoenix/coronavirus-in-arizona-officials-confirm-new-presumptive-positive-case |archive-date=March 4, 2020}}</ref> In New Hampshire, public health officials confirm a second case of coronavirus in an individual who made contact with the first case after the first case defied quarantine orders and attended a private event organized by [[Dartmouth College]]'s [[Tuck School of Business]] in [[White River Junction, Vermont]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.unionleader.com/news/health/coronavirus/second-case-of-coronavirus-in-nh-tests-positive/article_2da63bb4-818e-5774-a213-f40777cb0180.html |title=Second case of coronavirus in NH tests positive |last=Feely |first=Paul |date=March 3, 2020 |website=[[New Hampshire Union Leader]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304052458/https://www.unionleader.com/news/health/coronavirus/second-case-of-coronavirus-in-nh-tests-positive/article_2da63bb4-818e-5774-a213-f40777cb0180.html |archive-date=March 4, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/health/health-news/nh-coronavirus-patient-breaks-isolation-potentially-exposing-others-n1148641 |title=N.H. coronavirus patient breaks isolation, potentially exposing others |last=Edwards |first=Erika |date=March 3, 2020 |website=[[NBC]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304004726/https://www.nbcnews.com/health/health-news/nh-coronavirus-patient-breaks-isolation-potentially-exposing-others-n1148641 |archive-date=March 4, 2020}}</ref> New York officials announce the state's second confirmed case: a man in his 50s in [[New Rochelle]], [[Westchester County, New York|Westchester County]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.lohud.com/story/news/politics/politics-on-the-hudson/2020/03/03/coronavirus-new-york-westchester-man-has-states-second-confirmed-case/4937479002/ |title=Coronavirus in New York: Westchester man has state's second confirmed case |last=Campbell |first=Jon |date=March 3, 2020 |website=[[The Journal News]], White Plains, NY |url-status=live |access-date=March 3, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-03-03/nyc-school-closed-as-a-precaution-on-suspected-virus-case |title=New York Man Hospitalized With Coronavirus; Origin Unknown |last=Clukey |first=Keshia |date=March 3, 2020 |website=[[Bloomberg News|Bloomberg]] |url-status=live |access-date=March 3, 2020}}</ref> who had not recently traveled to any foreign countries affected by the outbreak.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://nypost.com/2020/03/03/bronx-jewish-day-school-closes-for-suspected-coronavirus-case/ |title=New York confirms second coronavirus case as Jewish schools close over virus fears |last=Algar |first=Selim |last2=Hogan |first2=Bernadette |date=March 3, 2020 |website=[[The New York Post]] |url-status=live |access-date=March 3, 2020 |last3=Steinbuch |first3=Yaron}}</ref> In [[North Carolina]], Governor [[Roy Cooper]] announces the state's first confirmed case: a person who had traveled to Washington and was \"exposed at a long term care facility.\" They are in stable condition and in isolation at their home.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/health/medical/live-first-case-of-coronavirus-confirmed-in-north-carolina-health-officials-say/ar-BB10Hs7e |title=First case of coronavirus confirmed in North Carolina, health officials say |publisher=MSN |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303210148/https://www.msn.com/en-us/health/medical/live-first-case-of-coronavirus-confirmed-in-north-carolina-health-officials-say/ar-BB10Hs7e |archive-date=March 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn March 4, the US [[Department of Homeland Security]] confirms that a \"contract medical screener\" for the CDC working at the [[Los Angeles International Airport]] tested positive for coronavirus. The individual is in self-isolation at home.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/health/health-news/medical-screener-lax-airport-tests-positive-coronavirus-n1149986 |title=Medical screener at LAX airport tests positive for coronavirus |last=Strickler |first=Laura |last2=Blankstein |first2=Andrew |date=March 4, 2020 |website=[[NBC]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305014721/https://www.nbcnews.com/health/health-news/medical-screener-lax-airport-tests-positive-coronavirus-n1149986 |archive-date=March 5, 2020}}</ref> New York officials confirm four new cases of coronavirus: the wife, son, and daughter of the second case, as well as the man's neighbor who drove him to the hospital. The new cases prompt the partial closure of the main campus of [[Yeshiva University]], where the man's son is a student, as well as the high school in the [[Bronx]] borough of New York City where the daughter is a student.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://newyork.cbslocal.com/2020/03/04/coronavirus-update-new-rochelle-man-self-quarantine/ |title=Coronavirus Update: 6 Cases Confirmed In N.Y. As Family, Neighbor Of Infected New Rochelle Man Test Positive For Virus |date=March 4, 2020 |publisher=[[WLNY]] |access-date=March 4, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.cnbc.com/2020/03/04/yeshiva-university-in-new-york-city-cancels-class-after-student-tests-positive-for-coronavirus.html |title=New York family of four all test positive for coronavirus as state cases climb |last=Feuer |first=William |date=March 4, 2020 |publisher=[[CNBC]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304210751/https://www.cnbc.com/2020/03/04/yeshiva-university-in-new-york-city-cancels-class-after-student-tests-positive-for-coronavirus.html |archive-date=March 4, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Gold |first=Michael |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/04/nyregion/coronavirus-nyc-yeshiva-university.html |title=Coronavirus in N.Y.: Family of Westchester Man and Neighbor Confirmed |date=March 4, 2020 |work=[[The New York Times]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304212724/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/04/nyregion/coronavirus-nyc-yeshiva-university.html |archive-date=March 4, 2020}}</ref> On the same day, another five confirmed cases are reported in a friend of the second case, as well as that friend's wife, two sons, and daughter.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.cnbc.com/2020/03/04/ny-gov-cuomo-confirms-5-new-cases-of-coronavirus-bringing-the-state-total-to-11.html |title=NY Gov. Cuomo confirms 5 new cases of coronavirus: 'This is literally like trying to stop air' |date=March 4, 2020 |publisher=[[WLNY]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304234936/https://www.cnbc.com/2020/03/04/ny-gov-cuomo-confirms-5-new-cases-of-coronavirus-bringing-the-state-total-to-11.html |archive-date=March 4, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://nypost.com/2020/03/04/five-more-new-york-coronavirus-cases-confirmed-bringing-state-total-to-11/ |title=Five more New York coronavirus cases confirmed, bringing state total to 11 |last=Hogan |first=Bernadette |last2=Feis |first2=Aaron |date=March 4, 2020 |website=[[The New York Post]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200308050724/https://nypost.com/2020/03/04/five-more-new-york-coronavirus-cases-confirmed-bringing-state-total-to-11/ |archive-date=March 8, 2020}}</ref>\n\n====March 5====\nNevada, Colorado, Tennessee, and Maryland announce their first cases, New Jersey announces a second presumptive case, while Washington announces 31 new cases.\n* [[Nevada]]: Public health officials in [[Las Vegas, Nevada|Las Vegas]] report that state's first confirmed case of coronavirus: a man in his 50s in [[Clark County, Nevada|Clark County]] who recently traveled to Washington state and Texas.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fox5vegas.com/news/local/health-district-confirms-first-presumptive-positive-novel-coronavirus-case-in/article_ebbb3984-5f04-11ea-8137-338faf13fedc.html |title=Health District confirms first 'presumptive positive' novel coronavirus case in Clark County |last=Emerson |first=Elaine |date=March 5, 2020 |publisher=[[KVVU]] |access-date=March 5, 2020}}</ref>  Also, public health officials announce a second confirmed case of coronavirus in [[Reno, Nevada|Reno]]. The new case, a man in his 50s, is in isolation at his home; the new case is linked to at least two other confirmed cases in [[Sonoma County, California]] and in [[Placer County, California]] among passengers who had been aboard the ''[[Grand Princess]]'' on a cruise from San Francisco to Mexico during the previous month.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.8newsnow.com/coronavirus/reno-man-tests-presumptive-positive-for-coronavirus-in-nevadas-second-case/ |title=Reno man tests 'presumptive positive' for coronavirus in Nevada's second case |last=Williams |first=Carolyn |date=March 6, 2020 |publisher=[[KLAS-TV|KLAS]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307134037/https://www.8newsnow.com/coronavirus/reno-man-tests-presumptive-positive-for-coronavirus-in-nevadas-second-case/ |archive-date=March 7, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.usnews.com/news/best-states/nevada/articles/2020-03-06/reno-case-of-coronavirus-is-2nd-for-nevada |title=Reno case of coronavirus is 2nd for Nevada |date=March 6, 2020 |website=[[Associated Press|AP]] via [[US News and World Report]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307134122/https://www.usnews.com/news/best-states/nevada/articles/2020-03-06/reno-case-of-coronavirus-is-2nd-for-nevada |archive-date=March 7, 2020 |access-date=March 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\n====March 6====\n[[File:2020-03-06 \u2014 Coronavirus \u2013 Flyers at Hartsfield-Jackson Atlanta International Airport wearing facemasks.jpg|thumb|Airline passengers at [[Hartsfield-Jackson Atlanta International Airport]] wearing facemasks]]\nTen states report their first case of coronavirus: Hawaii, Utah, Nebraska, Kentucky, Indiana, Minnesota, Connecticut, South Carolina, Pennsylvania, and Oklahoma. Many cases are associated with passengers from the ''Grand Princess'' cruise ship, which is being held off the California coast near San Francisco. Testing on the ship reveals 21 positives. The day also sees 6 deaths reported. Four are reported from Washington, by the hospital that treated patients from the LifeCare long-term care facility. Two are reported from Florida, and represent the third state (after Washington and California) with reported deaths. This brings the total deaths to 18, 15 in Washington, 1 in California, and 2 in Florida.\n\n<!-- unclear how cases on the ship should be treated, but cases on the Diamond Princess were considered separate from both the United Kingdom and Japan, and it appears the Grand Princess may have deliberately stayed outside territorial waters, so perhaps it shouldn't be included under California (or even the United States), especially since many other states have related cases -->\n* ''Grand Princess'': Twenty-one passengers on the ''Grand Princess'' cruise ship test positive for the coronavirus, 19 staff and 2 passengers.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://thehill.com/policy/healthcare/486394-pence-says-21-people-on-cruise-ship-off-california-have-coronavirus |title=Pence says 21 people on cruise ship off California tested positive for coronavirus |last=Swanson |first=Ian |date=March 6, 2020 |website=TheHill |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307025248/https://thehill.com/policy/healthcare/486394-pence-says-21-people-on-cruise-ship-off-california-have-coronavirus |archive-date=March 7, 2020 |access-date=March 6, 2020}}</ref>\n* Arizona: Public health officials announce the state's third case and first community transmission case in a [[Pinal County, Arizona|Pinal County]] woman.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.maricopa.gov/CivicAlerts.aspx?AID=1015 |title=Presumptive Positive Case of COVID-19 Identified in Pinal County. The case may signal community spread in Arizona |date=n.d. |website=Maricopa County, AZ |url-status=live |access-date=March 6, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Connecticut]]: Governor [[Ned Lamont]] confirm his state's first case of coronavirus in a hospital employee, a New York resident who is currently under self-quarantine back home in Westchester County, New York.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.courant.com/coronavirus/hc-br-connecticut-coronavirus-case-20200306-fxdj5smkgnf3jmgiuhn2coq22q-story.html |title=Gov. Lamont says Connecticut's first coronavirus case is an employee at Danbury Hospital who is now under self-quarantine |last=Fawcett |first=Zach Murdock, Alex Putterman, Eliza |website=courant.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307015150/https://www.courant.com/coronavirus/hc-br-connecticut-coronavirus-case-20200306-fxdj5smkgnf3jmgiuhn2coq22q-story.html |archive-date=March 7, 2020}}</ref>\n* Hawaii: Governor [[David Ige]] announces its first case of coronavirus, a resident that was a passenger of the ''Grand Princess'' which stopped in Hawaii in late February.<ref name=\"hawaii.1\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.khon2.com/coronavirus-2/gov-ige-confirms-first-case-of-coronavirus-in-hawaii/ |title=VIDEO: Hawaii resident, passenger aboard Grand Princess confirmed as first coronavirus case in Hawaii |date=March 7, 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307193138/https://www.khon2.com/coronavirus-2/gov-ige-confirms-first-case-of-coronavirus-in-hawaii/ |archive-date=March 7, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Indiana]]: The state reports its first case in an [[Indianapolis]] man who returned from travel to Boston.<ref>{{cite news |title=Indiana has 1st illness linked to coronavirus outbreak |url=https://apnews.com/85a65282ef8f2ca99ef4fab42b7da374 |accessdate=20 March 2020 |work=AP News |date=6 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320105659/https://apnews.com/85a65282ef8f2ca99ef4fab42b7da374 |archive-date=March 20, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* [[Kentucky]]: Governor [[Andy Beshear]] confirms the states first case, a [[Lexington, Kentucky|Lexington]] resident.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.kentucky.com/news/state/kentucky/article240970991.html |title=First case of Coronavirus confirmed in Kentucky, governor says |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306224123/https://www.kentucky.com/news/state/kentucky/article240970991.html |archive-date=March 6, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bizjournals.com/louisville/news/2020/03/06/first-kentucky-coronavirus-case-confirmed.html |title=First Kentucky coronavirus case confirmed |date=March 6, 2020 |access-date=March 7, 2020 |publisher=Louisville Business First}}</ref>\n* [[Minnesota]]: announces its first presumptive case, an elderly person, living in [[Ramsey County, Minnesota|Ramsey County]], who had been on a cruise ship recently.<!-- the official health department source does not state which cruise ship he was a passenger of, though it strongly suggests it was the ''grand princess'' by stating that it was a \"cruise ship with a known COVID-19 case\" (rather than \"many cases\" or something similar, as the seriousness of the ''grand princess'' cluster was not as well known at the time), while the hill appears to be the only source explicitly stating it was the ''diamond princess''--><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.health.state.mn.us/news/pressrel/2020/covid19030620.html |title=News release: Headline |website=health.state.mn.us |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200308144422/https://www.health.state.mn.us/news/pressrel/2020/covid19030620.html |archive-date=March 8, 2020}}</ref> The patient is reported to be in quarantine in their home.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://thehill.com/policy/healthcare/486392-minnesota-reports-first-presumptive-coronavirus-case |title=Minnesota reports first presumptive coronavirus case |date=2020-03-06 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307045918/https://thehill.com/policy/healthcare/486392-minnesota-reports-first-presumptive-coronavirus-case |archive-date=March 7, 2020}}</ref>\n* Nebraska: Governor [[Pete Ricketts]] announces the first presumptive positive case of coronavirus in Nebraska, a woman in her 30s from [[Douglas County, Nebraska|Douglas County]] who came back from England at the end of February.<ref name=\"nebraska.1\">{{Cite web |url=https://governor.nebraska.gov/press/first-presumptive-positive-case-coronavirus-2019-reported-nebraska-dhhs |title=First Presumptive Positive Case of Coronavirus 2019 Reported to Nebraska DHHS |website=governor.nebraska.gov |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307055941/https://governor.nebraska.gov/press/first-presumptive-positive-case-coronavirus-2019-reported-nebraska-dhhs |archive-date=March 7, 2020}}</ref> She was initially hospitalized at [[Methodist Hospital (Omaha, Nebraska)|Methodist Hospital]], and was being transferred to the Biocontainment Unit at the University of Nebraska Medical Center after her test result came back positive.<ref name=\"nebraska.1\" />\n* North Carolina: Public health officials announce a second confirmed case of coronavirus in a man in [[Chatham County, North Carolina|Chatham County]] who had recently traveled to Italy.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ncdhhs.gov/news/press-releases/north-carolina-identifies-second-case-covid-19 |title=North Carolina Identifies Second Case of COVID-19 |date=March 6, 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307051953/https://www.ncdhhs.gov/news/press-releases/north-carolina-identifies-second-case-covid-19 |archive-date=March 7, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.newsobserver.com/news/local/article240915536.html |title=New coronavirus case diagnosed in North Carolina, officials say |last=Banov |first=Jessica |last2=Johnson |first2=Anna |date=March 6, 2020 |website=[[The News & Observer]], Raleigh, N.C. |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307071415/https://www.newsobserver.com/news/local/article240915536.html |archive-date=March 7, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Oklahoma]]: Officials announce its first confirmed case of coronavirus in a [[Tulsa County, Oklahoma|Tulsa County]] man who had recently traveled to Italy.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.kjrh.com/news/local-news/first-case-of-coronavirus-confirmed-in-tulsa-county |title=First Case of Coronavirus Confirmed in Tulsa County |date=March 6, 2020 |publisher=KJRH |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307143525/https://www.kjrh.com/news/local-news/first-case-of-coronavirus-confirmed-in-tulsa-county |archive-date=March 7, 2020}}</ref>\n*Pennsylvania: Governor [[Tom Wolf]] announces the first two confirmed cases of coronavirus in [[Delaware County, Pennsylvania|Delaware County]] and in [[Wayne County, Pennsylvania|Wayne County]].\n* Rhode Island: The state confirms its third case, a woman who had contact with a positive case in New York in late February.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ri.gov/press/view/37858 |title=RIDOH's State Health Laboratories Identifies Third Case of COVID-19 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309185220/https://www.ri.gov/press/view/37858 |archive-date=March 9, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[South Carolina]] reports two presumptive cases in [[Kershaw County]] and [[Charleston County]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.live5news.com/2020/03/07/dhec-investigating-two-possible-cases-novel-coronavirus-south-carolina/ |title=DHEC investigating two possible cases of coronavirus in South Carolina |date=March 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\n====March 7====\nVirginia,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.13newsnow.com/article/news/health/coronavirus/first-coronavirus-case-confirmed-in-virginia/291-e5e3c430-be8d-45d7-b858-859fba98a01d |title=First coronavirus case confirmed in Virginia |last=136News Now Staff |date=March 7, 2020 |website=136News Now |publisher=[[WVEC|WVEC-TV]] |location=[[Hampton, Virginia]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200308192640/https://www.13newsnow.com/article/news/health/coronavirus/first-coronavirus-case-confirmed-in-virginia/291-e5e3c430-be8d-45d7-b858-859fba98a01d |archive-date=March 8, 2020}}</ref> Kansas, Missouri, and Washington, D.C.<ref name=\"DC\">{{Cite news |last=Hahn |first=Fritz |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/dc-md-va/2020/03/05/dc-coronavirus-tourism/ |title=Coronavirus closes Smithsonian museums, cancels some National Cherry Blossom Festival events |work=Going Out Guide |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313190830/https://www.washingtonpost.com/dc-md-va/2020/03/05/dc-coronavirus-tourism/ |archive-date=March 13, 2020 |quote=The District announced its first confirmed case of the coronavirus that causes covid-19 on March 7. On March 11, Mayor Muriel E. Bowser declared a state of emergency in the District, and the D.C. Health Department recommended that \"nonessential mass gatherings\" of more than 1,000 people should be canceled or postponed until March 31.}}</ref> announces its first cases. 1 new death is reported for March 7 in Washington. This brings the total confirmed US deaths due to coronavirus to 19, 16 in Washington, 1 in California, and 2 in Florida. In Pennsylvania, Governor Tom Wolf announces two new positive cases in [[Montgomery County, Pennsylvania|Montgomery County]]; both cases are related to travel within the United States.<ref>{{Cite news |last=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |url=https://6abc.com/health/2-montco-residents-test-presumptive-positive-for-covid-19/5993654/ |title=2 Montgomery County residents test presumptive positive for COVID-19 bringing state total to 4 |date=March 7, 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200308165356/https://6abc.com/health/2-montco-residents-test-presumptive-positive-for-covid-19/5993654/ |archive-date=March 8, 2020 |publisher=[[WPVI-TV|WPVI]] |location=Media, PA}}</ref>\n\n====March 8====\n[[Iowa]] and [[Vermont]] report their first cases of infection with the coronavirus. Three new deaths were reported in WA. This brought the total confirmed US deaths due to coronavirus to 22: 19 in Washington, 1 in California, and 2 in Florida.\n* Hawaii: Second case is reported by Governor David Ige and State health officials is an elderly man who tested positive after returning from travel to Washington state earlier in the month. He is hospitalized and in isolation at Kaiser Permanente' Moanalua medical facility.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Pang |first=Gordon |url=https://www.staradvertiser.com/2020/03/08/breaking-news/2nd-hawaii-resident-tests-positive-for-covid-19/ |title=Elderly man who recently traveled to Washington state becomes Hawaii's second coronavirus case |date=March 8, 2020 |work=Honolulu Star Advertiser |url-status=live}}</ref>\n* Indiana: Second and third cases are reported, both in [[Hendricks County, Indiana|Hendricks County]]. The third case is an elementary student, resulting in recommendation from Hendricks County Health Department for closure of Hickory Elementary school for two weeks beginning March 9. This is the first school closing to occur in Indiana due to the current outbreak.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theindychannel.com/coronavirus/second-case-of-coronavirus-confirmed-in-indiana-is-in-hendricks-county |title=Second case of coronavirus confirmed in Indiana is in Hendricks County |date=March 8, 2020 |access-date=March 8, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.wishtv.com/news/local-news/avon-elementary-student-tests-positive-for-coronavirus/ |title=Avon elementary student tests positive for coronavirus |date=March 8, 2020 |access-date=March 8, 2020}}</ref>\n* Iowa: Governor [[Kim Reynolds]] confirmed the state's first three positive cases in [[Johnson County, Iowa|Johnson County]].\n* Minnesota: The state of Minnesota reports 1 new case in [[Carver County]] and a total of 2 cases in Minnesota. The patient experienced symptoms on March 2, and is in the 50\u201359 age group. Thus far, both cases have been associated with travel.<ref name=\"StarT Carver Co.\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.startribune.com/minnesota-reports-second-covid-19-case/568614092/?refresh=true |title=Minnesota reports second coronavirus case, this one in Carver County |work=Star Tribune |access-date=March 8, 2020 |issue=March 8, 2020}}</ref>\n* South Carolina: 4 more presumptive positive cases, for a total of 6. One recently traveled to Italy, two are connected to a previous case, and one is of unknown origin.\n* Vermont: Vermont health officials announced the state's first \"presumptive positive\" case in [[Bennington County, Vermont|Bennington County]].\n\n====March 9====\nOhio governor [[Mike DeWine]] declares a state of emergency after Ohio reports its first cases of COVID-19.<ref name=\"10TV STATE OF EMERGENCY\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.10tv.com/article/3-confirmed-cases-coronavirus-ohio-dewine-declares-state-emergency-2020-mar |title=3 confirmed cases of coronavirus in Ohio; DeWine declares State of Emergency |date=March 9, 2020 |website=10TV}}</ref> As of March 9, Alabama, Alaska, Idaho, Maine, Michigan, Mississippi, New Mexico, North Dakota, South Dakota, and West Virginia have no cases, while Montana, Delaware, Wyoming and Arkansas have suspected cases. Washington reports 3 new deaths and California 1, bringing the number of US coronavirus deaths to 26.\n\nIt is reported that the Trump administration, without explanation, postponed the [[Director of National Intelligence]]'s (DNI) annual ''[[US World Wide Threat Assessment]]'' which warns that the U.S. remains unprepared for a global pandemic.  The office of the DNI was scheduled to deliver the ''Assessment'' to the [[United States House Permanent Select Committee on Intelligence|House Intelligence Committee]] on February 12.<ref>John Walcott [https://time.com/5799765/intelligence-report-pandemic-dangers The Trump Administration Is Stalling an Intel Report That Warns the U.S. Isn't Ready for a Global Pandemic] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313034152/https://time.com/5799765/intelligence-report-pandemic-dangers/ |date=March 13, 2020 }} March 9, 2020 TIME.com</ref>\n\n<!--Remember that a State/Local Government response should be also added to the State and local response section-->\n* Indiana: A case is reported in [[Noble County, Indiana|Noble County]], the state's 4th.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.indystar.com/story/news/health/2020/03/09/coronavirus-indiana-total-number-cases-state-now-4/5000639002/ |title=Person in northeast Indiana tests positive for coronavirus, bringing state total to 4 |date=March 9, 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310055242/https://www.indystar.com/story/news/health/2020/03/09/coronavirus-indiana-total-number-cases-state-now-4/5000639002/ |archive-date=March 10, 2020}}</ref>\n* Iowa: Five new presumptive positive cases are announced, bringing the statewide total to eight.  Governor [[Kim Reynolds]] signed a Proclamation of Disaster Emergency.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://kwwl.com/2020/03/09/kim-reynolds-signs-disaster-proclamation-due-to-the-coronavirus/ |title=Kim Reynolds signs disaster proclamation due to the coronavirus |date=March 9, 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310152524/https://kwwl.com/2020/03/09/kim-reynolds-signs-disaster-proclamation-due-to-the-coronavirus/ |archive-date=March 10, 2020 |access-date=March 13, 2020}}</ref>\n* Kentucky: Governor Andy Beshear confirms two new cases bringing the state's total to six.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.wkyt.com/content/news/SPECIAL-REPORT-Gov-Beshear-giving-update-on-coronavirus-cases-568624101.html |title=Two new coronavirus cases confirmed in Kentucky, total now six |date=March 9, 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313175426/https://www.wkyt.com/content/news/SPECIAL-REPORT-Gov-Beshear-giving-update-on-coronavirus-cases-568624101.html |archive-date=March 13, 2020}}</ref>\n* Missouri: St. Louis County Executive Dr. Sam Page reports that the father and younger sister of the state's first coronavirus patient violated a self-quarantine order, attending a father-daughter function for her high school, [[Villa Duchesne and Oak Hill School|Villa Duchesne]], at the Ritz-Carlton Hotel in Clayton. The pair also attended a party for students from both Villa and the [[John Burroughs School]] before heading to the hotel. Villa cancels classes following the announcement, and the Burroughs students in attendance at the party were asked to stay home from school until further notice; they are ultimately cleared by medical professionals in consultation with the school later the same week, and the Ritz-Carlton was to undergo substantial cleaning.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.stltoday.com/lifestyles/health-med-fit/coronavirus/family-of-missouri-s-first-coronavirus-patient-broke-self-quarantine/article_94fe6bf6-f679-5b88-870c-18c5f79d019b.html |title=Family of Missouri's first coronavirus patient broke self quarantine, St. Louis County officials say |last=Munz |first=Michele |website=STLtoday.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310140757/https://www.stltoday.com/lifestyles/health-med-fit/coronavirus/family-of-missouri-s-first-coronavirus-patient-broke-self-quarantine/article_94fe6bf6-f679-5b88-870c-18c5f79d019b.html |archive-date=March 10, 2020}}</ref>\n* North Carolina: 5 new presumptively positive cases are reported in [[Wake County]]. According to NCDHHS, all five had traveled to Boston in late February to attend a conference. This brings the total number of cases in North Carolina to 7.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://wlos.com/news/local/5-new-presumptively-positive-cases-of-the-coronavirus-in-nc |title=5 new presumptively positive cases of the coronavirus in North Carolina |date=March 9, 2020}}</ref>\n* Ohio: The [[Ohio State University]] suspends face-to-face instruction until March 30.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thelantern.com/2020/03/ohio-state-suspends-classes-until-march-30-due-to-coronavirus-outbreak |title=OHIO STATE SUSPENDS CLASSES UNTIL MARCH 30 DUE TO CORONAVIRUS OUTBREAK |last=Milnes |last2=Garrison |first2=Max |date=March 9, 2020 |website=thelantern.com |last3=Raudins |first3=Sam |access-date=March 18, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315065838/https://www.thelantern.com/2020/03/ohio-state-suspends-classes-until-march-30-due-to-coronavirus-outbreak/ |archive-date=March 15, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Governor Mike DeWine declares a state of emergency.<ref name=\"10TV STATE OF EMERGENCY\"/>\n* South Carolina: One additional presumptive positive case is reported, raising the total to 7.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thestate.com/news/state/south-carolina/article241030266.html|title=Total number of coronavirus cases in South Carolina rises to 7|first1=Lucas|last1=Daprile|first2=Sarah|last2=Ellis|date=March 9, 2020|website=thestate.com|access-date=March 20, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315194749/https://www.thestate.com/news/state/south-carolina/article241030266.html|archive-date=March 15, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Additionally, there is a \"possible\" case at [[Clemson University]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.counton2.com/health/coronavirus/clemson-health-officials-monitoring-possible-case-of-coronavirus/|title=Clemson health officials monitoring possible case of Coronavirus|date=March 9, 2020|website=counton2.com|access-date=March 20, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320175954/https://www.counton2.com/health/coronavirus/clemson-health-officials-monitoring-possible-case-of-coronavirus/|archive-date=March 20, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n====March 10====\n[[File:New Rochelle Containment Area March 2020.svg|right|thumb|Location of the [[New Rochelle]] Containment Area within [[Westchester County]], New York.]]\nSouth Dakota and Michigan reports their first cases. Mitigation measures expanded in New York, Massachusetts and Washington with a transition to online classes for universities and colleges and with the first semi-containment zone announced in New York. Two new deaths were reported in Washington and one death each reported in California, New Jersey, and South Dakota. This brought the total US deaths to 31 (24 WA, 3 CA, 2 FL, 1 NJ, 1 SD).\n*Massachusetts: Governor [[Charlie Baker]] declared a state of emergency as the number of cases doubled overnight, to 92. 70 of the cases are related to a meeting at [[Biogen]] in February. [[Harvard University]] ordered its students to vacate the campus by Sunday, March 15.<ref>[https://www.cnbc.com/2020/03/10/massachusetts-declares-emergency-as-coronavirus-cases-double-overnight-with-51-new-infections.html?recirc=taboolainternal Massachusetts declares emergency as coronavirus cases more than double overnight with 51 new infections] by Noah Higgins-Dunn, CNBC, 10 Mar 2020, retrieved 16 Mar 2020</ref>\n* Minnesota: A third case in the state is confirmed in [[Anoka County, Minnesota|Anoka County]]. The individual is in the 30\u201339-year-old range and had no reported underlying conditions. The resident is in critical condition. According to health officials, the case was not transmitted in the state and there is no evidence that the virus is spreading from person to person in Minnesota. [[Tim Walz|Gov. Tim Walz]] signed a $21&nbsp;million bill for funding COVID-19 preparedness.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.startribune.com/minnesota-confirms-third-covid-19-case-patient-is-hospitalized-in-critical-condition/568672732/ |title=Minnesota confirms third coronavirus case; patient is hospitalized in critical condition |website=Star Tribune |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311144250/http://www.startribune.com/minnesota-confirms-third-covid-19-case-patient-is-hospitalized-in-critical-condition/568672732/ |archive-date=March 11, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[South Dakota]]:  Health officials announce the state's first five confirmed cases and one death. The lone death tested positive for COVID-19, but the cause of death is still being investigated.<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.keloland.com/news/healthbeat/coronavirus/first-presumptive-positive-coronavirus-case-in-south-dakota/ |title=5 Coronavirus cases, one death in South Dakota |date=March 10, 2020 |access-date=March 13, 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312035323/https://www.keloland.com/news/healthbeat/coronavirus/first-presumptive-positive-coronavirus-case-in-south-dakota/ |archive-date=March 12, 2020}}</ref>\n\n====March 11====\nConfirmed coronavirus cases in the United States surpass 1,100.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/10/world/coronavirus-news.html |title=U.S. Cases of Coronavirus Surpass 1,000; British Health Minister Is Infected |work=The New York Times |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310234022/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/10/world/coronavirus-news.html |archive-date=March 10, 2020}}</ref> Arkansas, Delaware, Mississippi, New Mexico, North Dakota and Wyoming reported their first cases. More universities and colleges suspend classes or move to remote-access teaching. Washington governor [[Jay Inslee]] orders a halt to all gatherings of greater than 250 in three counties, while Ohio governor [[Mike DeWine]] orders all public gatherings of more than 1,000 people to be banned statewide. Five new deaths are reported in Washington and one death in California. This brings the total US deaths to 37 (29 WA, 4 CA, 2 FL, 1 NJ, 1 SD).\n* Connecticut: Several towns in Connecticut announce schools will close for at least two weeks beginning March 12, including [[New Canaan, Connecticut|New Canaan]], where the state's third case was confirmed.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nbcconnecticut.com/news/local/new-canaan-schools-to-close-for-14-days-due-to-coronavirus/2236728/ |title=New Canaan Schools to Close for 14 Days Due to Coronavirus |access-date=March 13, 2020}}</ref>\n* Florida: A man wearing a mask and gloves with symptoms who knowingly tested positive for Coronavirus boards a [[JetBlue]] plane from [[JFK Airport]] with his knowing wife to [[PBI Airport]] in [[West Palm Beach, FL]], potentially exposing both airports and an entire plane to the virus. Despite this, Florida officials release all passengers without requiring isolation or testing.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.wptv.com/news/region-c-palm-beach-county/west-palm-beach/health-department-investigating-medical-situation-on-flight-to-pbia |title=Passenger who arrived at Palm Beach International Airport tests positive for coronavirus |date=March 12, 2020 |publisher=WPTV |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312120923/https://www.wptv.com/news/region-c-palm-beach-county/west-palm-beach/health-department-investigating-medical-situation-on-flight-to-pbia |archive-date=March 12, 2020}}</ref>\n* Indiana: The state had 5 more cases, bringing the total to 11.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.usnews.com/news/best-states/indiana/articles/2020-03-11/4-new-covid-19-cases-in-indiana-state-now-has-10-cases |title=Archived copy |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313024322/https://www.usnews.com/news/best-states/indiana/articles/2020-03-11/4-new-covid-19-cases-in-indiana-state-now-has-10-cases |archive-date=March 13, 2020}}</ref> The [[University of Notre Dame]] announce that in-person classes will be suspended and moved online until at least April 13.<ref name=\"ND\">{{Cite web |url=https://news.nd.edu/news/notre-dame-switches-to-online-after-canceling-in-person-classes/ |title=Notre Dame switches to online after canceling in-person classes |last=Dame |first=Marketing Communications: Web // University of Notre |website=Notre Dame News}}</ref>\n* [[Maine]]: The [[University of Maine]] in [[Orono, Maine|Orono]] announce that in-person classes wil be cancelled for the remainder of the semester beginning March 23, and that all classes will be transitioned to online only. In addition, all students living on campus were required to be moved out by March 22.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://umaine.edu/emergency/coronavirus/ |title=UMaine/UMM coronavirus response frequently asked questions, March 12 \u2013 Emergency Information \u2013 University of Maine |access-date=March 13, 2020}}</ref>\n* Minnesota: The [[University of Minnesota]] announce that all in-person classes will be suspended until at least April 1 following spring break.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://minnesota.cbslocal.com/2020/03/11/coronavirus-minnesota-university-classes-suspended-canceled/ |title=Coronavirus in Minnesota: U Of M, UW-Madison Among Universities Suspending In-Person Classes |date=March 11, 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312180101/https://minnesota.cbslocal.com/2020/03/11/coronavirus-minnesota-university-classes-suspended-canceled/ |archive-date=March 12, 2020}}</ref> Two more cases were confirmed, bringing the total number of cases to five.<ref name=\":6\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.health.state.mn.us/diseases/coronavirus/situation.html |title=Situation Update for Coronavirus Disease 2019 (COVID-19) \u2013 Minnesota Dept. of Health |website=health.state.mn.us |access-date=March 17, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309021508/https://www.health.state.mn.us/diseases/coronavirus/situation.html |archive-date=March 9, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>[[Mayo Clinic]] in [[Rochester, MN|Rochester]] began \"drive-through testing\" for the virus, though patients still needed to be approved to be tested by telephone screening.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.postbulletin.com/life/health/mayo-clinic-starts-drive-thru-testing-for-covid/article_0087a856-63e3-11ea-be76-c7558f932526.html |title=Mayo Clinic starts drive-thru testing for COVID-19 |access-date=March 16, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315124156/https://www.postbulletin.com/life/health/mayo-clinic-starts-drive-thru-testing-for-covid/article_0087a856-63e3-11ea-be76-c7558f932526.html |archive-date=March 15, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* Missouri: [[Washington University in Saint Louis]] announces a switch to online classes until at least late April and asked undergraduates to go home by March 15. [[University of Missouri|University of Missouri's Columbia campus]] cancels classes March 12 and 13 and directs that in-person classes should be taught by other means for March 16 through 20 (prior to the March 21 through 29 spring recess).\n* Mississippi: Health officials report the state's first case, a man who had recently traveled to Florida.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://msdh.ms.gov/msdhsite/_static/23,21819,341.html |title=Mississippi Reports First Positive Case of Coronavirus \u2013 Mississippi State Department of Health |website=msdh.ms.gov |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312133123/https://msdh.ms.gov/msdhsite/_static/23,21819,341.html |archive-date=March 12, 2020}}</ref>\n* New Mexico: 3 presumptive positive cases, a couple in their 60s who recently traveled to Egypt and one in her 70s who recently traveled to the New York City area.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.krqe.com/health/coronavirus-new-mexico/three-presumptive-cases-of-coronavirus-confirmed-in-new-mexico/ |title=Three presumptive cases of coronavirus confirmed in New Mexico |publisher=KRQE |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311172039/https://www.krqe.com/health/coronavirus-new-mexico/three-presumptive-cases-of-coronavirus-confirmed-in-new-mexico/ |archive-date=March 11, 2020}}</ref>\n* Oklahoma: [[NBA]] player [[Rudy Gobert]] tested positive for COVID-19 prior to the game between the [[Utah Jazz]] and the [[Oklahoma City Thunder]] at [[Chesapeake Energy Arena]] in [[Oklahoma City]]. The game was postponed and the NBA announced that the [[2019\u201320 NBA season]] would be suspended.\n* South Dakota: Three presumptive positive cases, bringing state total to eight.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.keloland.com/news/healthbeat/coronavirus/noem-to-hold-covid-19-news-conference-wednesday-afternoon/ |title=LATEST: CDC announces $4.6 million in COVID-19 funding to South Dakota; Noem to hold media briefing |website=KELOLAND |publisher=KELOLAND |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312034133/https://www.keloland.com/news/healthbeat/coronavirus/noem-to-hold-covid-19-news-conference-wednesday-afternoon/ |archive-date=March 12, 2020}}</ref>\n\n====March 12====\nTotal US cases passed 1,500. More universities and colleges transitioned to online attendance across the country. Public school closures are announced in Arkansas, Colorado, Connecticut, Kentucky, Maryland, Massachusetts, Michigan, New Mexico, Ohio, Utah, Virginia and Washington state. Georgia and Kansas report their first deaths and Washington state reports 2 additional deaths. This brings the total US deaths to 41 (31 WA, 4 CA, 2 FL, 1 NJ, 1 SD, 1 GA, 1 KS).\n\nMost major sports leagues, including [[Major League Soccer|MLS]], the [[NHL]], and the [[National Lacrosse League]], announce the suspension of their seasons that are already in progress. The [[XFL (2020)|XFL]] terminates its [[2020 XFL season|inaugural season]], while [[Major League Baseball]] announces the cancellation of all remaining [[spring training]] games and delays the start of their [[2020 MLB season|2020 season]]. In addition, the [[NCAA]] cancels all postseason tournaments in their winter and spring sports, which includes the [[2020 NCAA Division I Men's Basketball Tournament|men's]] and [[2020 NCAA Division I Women's Basketball Tournament|women's]] basketball tournaments, as well as the [[2020 NCAA Division I Baseball Tournament|baseball]] and [[2020 NCAA Division I Softball Tournament|softball]] tournaments. The cancellation of the basketball tournament marks the first time the tournament will not be held due to unforeseen circumstances.\n* Alabama: Despite having no recorded cases in the state, the [[University of Alabama System]] as well as [[Auburn University]] both announced they are transitioning to online remote attendance when courses resume from spring break.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://uasystem.edu/updated-interim-emergency-policy-for-ua-uab-and-uah/ |title=Updated Interim Emergency Policy for UA, UAB and UAH |publisher=University of Alabama System |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312225239/http://uasystem.edu/updated-interim-emergency-policy-for-ua-uab-and-uah/ |archive-date=March 12, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://ocm.auburn.edu/newsroom/news_articles/2020/03/121240-coronavirus-remote-transition.php |title=Auburn University to transition to remote instruction March 16 \u2013 April 10 |publisher=Auburn University |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312193041/https://ocm.auburn.edu/newsroom/news_articles/2020/03/121240-coronavirus-remote-transition.php |archive-date=March 12, 2020}}</ref>\n* Alaska: State officials announced the first positive case of coronavirus in the state.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.adn.com/alaska-news/2020/03/13/first-positive-alaska-coronavirus-case-identified/ |title=First positive Alaska coronavirus case identified |date=March 12, 2020 |publisher=Anchorage Daily News |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313064058/https://www.adn.com/alaska-news/2020/03/13/first-positive-alaska-coronavirus-case-identified/ |archive-date=March 13, 2020}}</ref>\n* Colorado: The first school districts in the state, including [[Denver Public Schools]], announced closures. An employee at [[University of Colorado Boulder]] tested positive for coronavirus. The [[Colorado Department of Corrections]] suspended in-person visitation in state prisons. The state reported 11 new cases.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.cpr.org/2020/03/12/colorado-coronavirus-updates-closures-testing-cases-school/ |title=Coronavirus in Colorado: What's going on today |last=Colorado Public Radio Staff |date=2020-03-12 |website=Colorado Public Radio |access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n* Connecticut: A number of school districts announced closures beginning on March 13 through at least March 27, including those in the cities of [[Bridgeport, Connecticut|Bridgeport]], [[New Haven, Connecticut|New Haven]], and [[Stamford, Connecticut|Stamford]], among several others.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nbcconnecticut.com/weather/school-closings/ |title=School Closings \u2013 Connecticut News, Local News, Weather, Traffic, Entertainment, Breaking News |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200101074233/https://www.nbcconnecticut.com/weather/school-closings/ |archive-date=January 1, 2020}}</ref>\n* Delaware: Governor [[John Carney (politician)|John Carney]] declared a state of emergency following the announcement of three more cases, connected with the University of Delaware.\n* Hawaii: The [[University of Hawaii]] announced classes at all campuses will be held online beginning March 23.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.hawaii.edu/news/2020/03/12/uh-actions-address-covid-19/ |title=University of Hawaii actions to address COVID-19 pandemic &#124; University of Hawai\u02bbi System News |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313193051/https://www.hawaii.edu/news/2020/03/12/uh-actions-address-covid-19/ |archive-date=March 13, 2020}}</ref>\n* Indiana: Went from 11 to 12 cases. Gov. Holcomb Announces New Steps to Protect Public.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://calendar.in.gov/site/gov/event/gov-holcomb-announces-new-steps-to-protect-public-from-covid-19/ |title=Gov. Holcomb Announces New Steps to Protect Public from COVID-19 |website=calendar.in.gov}}</ref>\n* Maine: Maine governor [[Janet Mills]] announced the state's first confirmed case of the virus, a woman in her 50s in [[Androscoggin County]]. The woman is said to be quarantined inside her home.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.foxnews.com/health/maine-confirms-first-coronavirus-case |title=Maine confirms first coronavirus case, patient is quarantined at home |last=Hein |first=Alexandria |date=March 12, 2020 |publisher=Fox News Channel |access-date=March 13, 2020}}</ref>\n* Minnesota: The Minnesota Department of Health has confirmed nine total cases in the state, affecting [[Anoka County, Minnesota|Anoka]], [[Carver County, Minnesota|Carver]], [[Dakota County, Minnesota|Dakota]], [[Hennepin County, Minnesota|Hennepin]], [[Olmsted County, Minnesota|Olmsted]], [[Ramsey County, Minnesota|Ramsey]], and [[Stearns County, Minnesota|Stearns]] counties.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.health.state.mn.us/diseases/coronavirus/situation.html |title=Situation Update for Coronavirus Disease 2019 (COVID-19) |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309021508/https://www.health.state.mn.us/diseases/coronavirus/situation.html |archive-date=March 9, 2020}}</ref>\n* New Mexico:  All public schools in the state will be closed for three weeks starting Monday, March 16.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.governor.state.nm.us/2020/03/12/new-mexico-schools-to-temporarily-close/ |title=New Mexico schools to temporarily close &#124; Office of the Governor \u2013 Michelle Lujan Grisham |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313081615/https://www.governor.state.nm.us/2020/03/12/new-mexico-schools-to-temporarily-close/ |archive-date=March 13, 2020}}</ref>\n* Ohio: The Ohio State University suspends all face-to-face classes for the rest of the spring semester. Spring break is extended until March 22 so that faculty have time to prepare. Students living in residence halls are to begin moving out.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thelantern.com/2020/03/university-announces-virtual-instruction-for-rest-of-semester-early-move-out-of-residence-halls/ |title=University Announces Virtual Instruction For Rest of Semester, Early Move-Out of Residence Halls |last=Long |first=Jack |last2=Milnes |first2=Owen |date=March 12, 2020 |website=thelantern.com |last3=Szilagy |first3=Sarah |last4=Raudins |first4=Sam |access-date=March 18, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317191452/https://www.thelantern.com/2020/03/university-announces-virtual-instruction-for-rest-of-semester-early-move-out-of-residence-halls/ |archive-date=March 17, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Mike DeWine is the first governor to announce statewide school closings.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.axios.com/ohio-governor-bars-restaurants-coronavirus-26e4b6e3-7f65-4f6a-abf9-f3940220cc6f.html |title=States order bars and restaurants to close due to coronavirus |last=Basu |first=Zachary |website=Axios |access-date=March 16, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316084429/https://www.axios.com/ohio-governor-bars-restaurants-coronavirus-26e4b6e3-7f65-4f6a-abf9-f3940220cc6f.html |archive-date=March 16, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Starting on March 16 all K-12 schools in Ohio will be closed for 3 weeks.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nbc4i.com/news/local-news/coronavirus-in-ohio-governor-orders-schools-to-take-extended-spring-breaks-starting-monday/ |title=Coronavirus in Ohio: Governor orders schools to take extended spring breaks starting Monday |date=March 12, 2020 |website=NBC4 WCMH-TV |access-date=March 12, 2020}}</ref> DeWine also bans \"mass gatherings\" of 100 or more people.<ref name= \"CBS10 TIMELINE\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.10tv.com/article/ohio-barbershops-hair-and-nail-salons-ordered-close-amid-coronavirus-concerns-2020-mar|title=Ohio barbershops, hair and nail salons ordered to close amid coronavirus concerns|date=March 18, 2010|website=10tv.com|access-date=March 18, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318232922/https://www.10tv.com/article/ohio-barbershops-hair-and-nail-salons-ordered-close-amid-coronavirus-concerns-2020-mar|archive-date=March 18, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n====March 13====\nTotal U.S. cases passed 2,100. Colorado reported its first death,<ref>{{Cite news |last=Seaman |first=Jessica |url=https://www.denverpost.com/2020/03/13/colorado-coronavirus-death/ |title=Colorado confirms first coronavirus death since outbreak hit state last week |date=2020-03-13 |work=The Denver Post |access-date=2020-03-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318054827/https://www.denverpost.com/2020/03/13/colorado-coronavirus-death/ |archive-date=March 18, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Florida and California both reported an additional death, and Washington state reported 6 additional deaths. This brought the total number of deaths in the US to 50 (37 WA, 5 CA, 3 FL, 1 NJ, 1 SD, 1 GA, 1 KS, 1 CO). The [[National Hockey League|NHL]] (National Hockey League) asked players to self-quarantine for a week or more in an attempt to save the season.<ref>[https://www.tsn.ca/nhl-urges-players-to-self-quarantine-to-help-save-season-1.1457233 NHL urges players to \u2018self-quarantine\u2019 to help save season] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317193559/https://www.tsn.ca/nhl-urges-players-to-self-quarantine-to-help-save-season-1.1457233 |date=March 17, 2020 }}, TSN, Frank Seravalli, March 13, 2020.</ref>\n\nLater that day, President [[Donald Trump]] took a COVID-19 test after coming into contact with several people who had contracted the disease and found to be negative.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://abcnews.go.com/US/coronavirus-live-updates-house-passes-coronavirus-pandemic-stimulus/story?id=69593951 |title=Coronavirus live updates: Trump says he took test; travel ban extended to UK, Ireland |date=March 14, 2020 |work=ABC News |url-status=live |access-date=March 18, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314222831/https://abcnews.go.com/US/coronavirus-live-updates-house-passes-coronavirus-pandemic-stimulus/story?id=69593951 |archive-date=March 14, 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2020/mar/14/trump-coronavirus-paid-sick-leave-unemployment-testing |title=Trump says he took coronavirus test and expands travel ban to UK and Ireland |date=March 14, 2020 |work=The Guardian |url-status=live |access-date=March 18, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314224603/https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2020/mar/14/trump-coronavirus-paid-sick-leave-unemployment-testing |archive-date=March 14, 2020 }}</ref> On March 13 the House passed an [https://www.congress.gov/bill/116th-congress/house-bill/6201?s=1&r=88 aid package] for workers and individuals that was supported by President Trump.<ref>[https://www.newsweek.com/40-house-republicans-reject-paid-sick-leave-combat-coronavirus-pandemic-1491988?fbclid=IwAR0uw1yoA7-J5VS5dScaZeuxdg5Jer5ApHfQZWIdTmfr24pgW7jHcjSweNA 40 HOUSE REPUBLICANS REJECT PAID SICK LEAVE TO COMBAT CORONAVIRUS PANDEMIC] BY RAMSEY TOUCHBERRY, Newsweek, 14 Mar 2020</ref>\n\nIn a March 13, 2020 report \"not for public distribution\", the [[United States Department of Health and Human Services]] (HHS) used the working assumptions for their response plan, that the COVID-19 \"pandemic will last 18 months or longer and could include multiple waves of illness\", and that resultant \"supply chain and transportation impacts\" would \"likely result in significant shortages\".<ref>{{cite news |last1=Bernstein |first1=Leandra |title=Government report anticipates 18-month pandemic, 'significant shortages' |url=https://komonews.com/news/nation-world/government-report-anticipates-18-month-pandemic-significant-shortages |accessdate=March 24, 2020 |work=[[Sinclair Broadcast Group]] |date=March 20, 2020}}</ref>\n* Alabama: First case announced in Montgomery County.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.waff.com/2020/03/13/governor-ivey-releases-statement-alabamas-first-confirmed-coronavirus-case/|title=WAFF48: First case of COVID-19 confirmed in Alabama|date=March 13, 2020|website=waff.com}}</ref>\n* Georgia: Governor Brian Kemp declared a public health emergency in the state of Georgia.<ref name=\":3a\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.wsbtv.com/news/georgia/gov-kemp-declare-public-health-emergency-call-special-session/F4ZAZ67SKZAC5ITRZGYGA5JKJE/ |title=Gov. Kemp declares public health emergency; calls for special session |last=WSBTV com News Staff |website=WSBTV |language=en-US |access-date=2020-03-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319210849/https://www.wsbtv.com/news/georgia/gov-kemp-declare-public-health-emergency-call-special-session/F4ZAZ67SKZAC5ITRZGYGA5JKJE/ |archive-date=March 19, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* [[Idaho]]: The state's first confirmed case of the virus was announced, a woman in her 50s who recently traveled to New York.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ktvb.com/article/news/health/coronavirus/idaho-confirms-first-covid-19-coronavirus-case/277-262de30b-ef00-40a2-b40e-43e26f0bb99b |title=Watch Live: First Idaho case of coronavirus confirmed, Gov. Brad Little to provide more details |last=Miller |