nd [[Wright County, MN|Wright]].<ref name=\"bringmethenews.com\" /> Governor Tim Walz has ordered the closure of public places, including all: restaurants, bars, coffee shops, gyms, theaters, breweries, ski resorts, and other public places until at least March 27. Bars and restaurants in the state were closed only to dine in customers; the businesses were allowed to continue to serve customers by take out or delivery orders. He said this order may be extended.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.mprnews.org/story/2020/03/16/walz-covid19-bar-restaurant-closure-and-unemployment-help |title=Walz temporarily closes bars, restaurants and gyms to curb COVID-19 spread |last=MPR Staff |website=Minnesota Public Radio |access-date=17 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317231710/https://www.mprnews.org/story/2020/03/16/walz-covid19-bar-restaurant-closure-and-unemployment-help |archive-date=March 17, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* Ohio: The state has 50 confirmed cases of COVID-19. Bowling alleys, fitness centers, gyms, movie theaters, public recreation centers, trampoline parks, and water parks are ordered to be shut<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.dispatch.com/news/20200316/coronavirus-gov-mike-dewine-closes-gyms-recreation-centers |title=Coronavirus: Gov. Mike DeWine closes gyms, recreation centers |last=Wagner |first=Mike |date=March 16, 2020 |website=dispatch.com |access-date=March 18, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318061227/https://www.dispatch.com/news/20200316/coronavirus-gov-mike-dewine-closes-gyms-recreation-centers |archive-date=March 18, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> and gatherings of more than 50 people are banned.<ref name= \"CBS10 TIMELINE\"/> DeWine announces the [[United States presidential primary|presidential primary elections]], scheduled for the next day, will be cancelled on orders of Department of Health director Amy Acton.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/17/politics/primary-elections-coronavirus/