xcept for those providing \"essential services\" (such as groceries, hospitals, pharmacies, banks, or delivery services), \"essential infrastructure\" (such as utilities or public transportation), or \"essential government functions\".<ref>{{Cite news |last=Har |first=Janie |url=https://apnews.com/a342998638cdccb56172a1663e8d6edf |title=San Francisco Bay Area counties issue shelter-in-place order |date=2020-03-16 |work=AP News |access-date=March 18, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318024109/https://apnews.com/a342998638cdccb56172a1663e8d6edf |archive-date=March 18, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Arango |first=Tim |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/16/us/california-covid-19.html |title=To Battle Virus, 6 California Counties Order Everyone to Stay Home |date=2020-03-16 |work=The New York Times |access-date=2020-03-17 |last2=Fuller |first2=Thomas |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331 |last3=Eligon |first3=John |last4=Dougherty |first4=Conor |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318041903/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/16/us/california-covid-19.html |archive-date=March 18, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n*Florida: Governor of Florida announces it has 24 new cases, increasing the total to 216 cases.<ref name=\"Cutway\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.clickorlando.com/news/local/2020/03/17/florida-coronavirus-cases-swells-to-216-governor-says/|title=Number of Florida coronavirus cases swells to 216, governor says|last=Cutway|first=Adrienne|date=2020-03-17|website=WKMG|language=en|access-date=2020-03-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318140035/https://www.clickorlando.com/news/local/2020/03/17/florida-coronavirus-cases-swells-to-216-governor-says/|archive-date=March 18, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The governor also orders businesses that sell liquor to reduce their occupancy by a half, and to limit parties on beaches to only 10 people per group.<ref name=\"Cutway\"/>\n* Kansas: [[Laura Kelly|Governor Laura Kelly]] ord