ive.org/web/20200320205626/https://www.koin.com/news/health/governor-brown-extends-school-closure-to-april-28/|archive-date=March 20, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*South Dakota: Closure of K-12 schools extended an extra week. Set to resume on March, 30.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.keloland.com/news/healthbeat/coronavirus/gov-noem-gives-covid-19-update-in-sioux-falls-tuesday/ |title=Gov. Noem: South Dakota schools to remain closed for another week |date=2020-03-17 |website=KELOLAND.com |language=en-US |access-date=2020-03-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318081507/https://www.keloland.com/news/healthbeat/coronavirus/gov-noem-gives-covid-19-update-in-sioux-falls-tuesday/ |archive-date=March 18, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n*Texas: The second death in Texas is reported. A resident of a retirement community in Arlington died on Sunday, March 15.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nbcdfw.com/news/coronavirus/arlington-resident-dies-from-coronavirus-first-in-north-texas/2333046/|title=Arlington Resident Dies From Coronavirus, First in North Texas|accessdate=Mar 19, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319042244/https://www.nbcdfw.com/news/coronavirus/arlington-resident-dies-from-coronavirus-first-in-north-texas/2333046/|archive-date=March 19, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*Virginia: Governor Northam announces a ban on gatherings of more than 10 people. 15 new cases are reported, bringing the total to 67 cases in Virginia.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.wsls.com/news/virginia/2020/03/17/15-new-coronavirus-cases-in-virginia-now-67-total-cases/ |title=15 new coronavirus cases in Virginia, now 67 total cases |last=Williamson |first=Jeff |date=2020-03-17 |website=WSLS |language=en |access-date=2020-03-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318041135/https://www.wsls.com/news/virginia/2020/03/17/15-new-coronavirus-cases-in-virginia-now-67-total-cases/ |archive-date=March 18, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> \n*[[West Virginia]]: Confirm